built with pdoc

aiobungie

A Pythonic async/await wrapper for interacting with the Bungie API.

Base client.

Example
import aiobungie

client = aiobungie.Client('YOUR_API_KEY')

# Search for Destiny2 users.
async def main() -> None:
    users = await client.search_users('Crit')

    # Iterate over the users and take the first 5 results.
    for user in users.take(5):
        print(f'{user.name} ({user.code})')

        # Iterate through the users memberships.
        for membership in user.memberships:
            print(membership.type, membership.id)

client.run(main()) # or asyncio.run(main())

Single RESTClient instance.

The difference between base client and the REST clients:

  • No Hight-Level concepts.
  • All returned data are pure JSON objects from the API.
  • No runtime assertions.
Example
import aiobungie

async def main() -> None:
    # Using `async with` context manager to close the session properly.
    async with aiobungie.RESTClient("TOKEN") as rest:
        payload = await rest.fetch_player('Fate怒', 4275)

        for membership in payload:
            print(membership['membershipId'], membership['iconPath'])

import asyncio
asyncio.run(main())

REST client pool.

A REST client pool allows you to acquire multiple RESTClient instances that shares the same connection.

Example
import aiobungie
import asyncio

pool = aiobungie.RESTPool("token")

async def func1() -> None:
    async with pool.acquire() as instance:
        tokens = await instance.fetch_oauth2_tokens('code')
        pool.metadata['tokens'] = tokens

# Other instance may access the tokens from pool since its shared.

async def func2() -> None:
    async with pool.acquire() as instance:
        tokens = pool.metadata['tokens']
        tokens = await instance.refresh_access_token(tokens.refresh_token)

async def main() -> None:
    await asyncio.gather(func1(), func2())

asyncio.run(main())

Should you use the base client or the REST client? This returns to you. For an example if you're building a website.

You can use python as a REST API in the backend with the RESTClient since all returned object are JSON objects. Which gives you the freedom to deserialize it and implement your own logic in the front-end.

Or of you're building a Discord bot for an example or something simple. The base client is the way to go.

 22"""A Pythonic `async`/`await` wrapper for interacting with the Bungie API.
 23
 24Base client.
 25
 26Example
 27-------
 28```py
 29import aiobungie
 30
 31client = aiobungie.Client('YOUR_API_KEY')
 32
 33# Search for Destiny2 users.
 34async def main() -> None:
 35    users = await client.search_users('Crit')
 36
 37    # Iterate over the users and take the first 5 results.
 38    for user in users.take(5):
 39        print(f'{user.name} ({user.code})')
 40
 41        # Iterate through the users memberships.
 42        for membership in user.memberships:
 43            print(membership.type, membership.id)
 44
 45client.run(main()) # or asyncio.run(main())
 46```
 47
 48Single RESTClient instance.
 49
 50The difference between base client and the REST clients:
 51
 52* No Hight-Level concepts.
 53* All returned data are pure JSON objects from the API.
 54* No runtime assertions.
 55
 56Example
 57-------
 58```py
 59import aiobungie
 60
 61async def main() -> None:
 62    # Using `async with` context manager to close the session properly.
 63    async with aiobungie.RESTClient("TOKEN") as rest:
 64        payload = await rest.fetch_player('Fate怒', 4275)
 65
 66        for membership in payload:
 67            print(membership['membershipId'], membership['iconPath'])
 68
 69import asyncio
 70asyncio.run(main())
 71```
 72
 73REST client pool.
 74
 75A REST client pool allows you to acquire multiple `RESTClient` instances that shares the same connection.
 76
 77Example
 78-------
 79```py
 80import aiobungie
 81import asyncio
 82
 83pool = aiobungie.RESTPool("token")
 84
 85async def func1() -> None:
 86    async with pool.acquire() as instance:
 87        tokens = await instance.fetch_oauth2_tokens('code')
 88        pool.metadata['tokens'] = tokens
 89
 90# Other instance may access the tokens from pool since its shared.
 91
 92async def func2() -> None:
 93    async with pool.acquire() as instance:
 94        tokens = pool.metadata['tokens']
 95        tokens = await instance.refresh_access_token(tokens.refresh_token)
 96
 97async def main() -> None:
 98    await asyncio.gather(func1(), func2())
 99
100asyncio.run(main())
101```
102
103Should you use the base client or the REST client?
104This returns to you. For an example if you're building a website.
105
106You can use python as a REST API in the backend with the RESTClient since all returned object are JSON objects.
107Which gives you the freedom to deserialize it and implement your own logic in the front-end.
108
109Or of you're building a Discord bot for an example or something simple. The base client is the way to go.
110"""
111

#   class Client(aiobungie.traits.ClientApp):
View Source 
  60class Client(traits.ClientApp):
  61    """Standard Bungie API client application.
  62
  63    This client deserialize the REST JSON responses using `aiobungie.internal.factory.Factory`
  64    and returns `aiobungie.crate` Python object implementations of the responses.
  65
  66    A `aiobungie.RESTClient` REST client can also be used alone for low-level concepts.
  67
  68    Parameters
  69    -----------
  70    token: `str`
  71        Your Bungie's API key or Token from the developer's portal.
  72
  73    Other Parameters
  74    ----------------
  75    rest_client: `aiobungie.interfaces.RESTInterface | None`
  76        An optional rest client instance you can pass.
  77        If set to `None` then the client will use the default instance.
  78
  79    Example
  80    -------
  81    ```py
  82    TOKEN = "SOME_TOKEN"
  83    async with aiobungie.RESTClient(TOKEN, max_retries=2) as rest_client:
  84        client = aiobungie.Client(TOKEN, rest_client=rest_client)
  85    ```
  86
  87    max_retries : `int`
  88        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `5xx` status code.
  89    max_ratelimit_retries : `int`
  90        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `429` status code. Defaults to `3`.
  91    client_secret : `str | None`
  92        An optional application client secret,
  93        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  94    client_id : `int | None`
  95        An optional application client id,
  96        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  97    """
  98
  99    __slots__ = ("_rest", "_factory", "_client_secret", "_client_id")
 100
 101    def __init__(
 102        self,
 103        token: str,
 104        /,
 105        client_secret: typing.Optional[str] = None,
 106        client_id: typing.Optional[int] = None,
 107        *,
 108        rest_client: typing.Optional[interfaces.RESTInterface] = None,
 109        max_retries: int = 4,
 110        max_ratelimit_retries: int = 3,
 111    ) -> None:
 112
 113        self._client_secret = client_secret
 114        self._client_id = client_id
 115
 116        self._rest = (
 117            rest_client
 118            if rest_client is not None
 119            else rest_.RESTClient(
 120                token,
 121                client_secret,
 122                client_id,
 123                max_retries=max_retries,
 124                max_ratelimit_retries=max_ratelimit_retries,
 125            )
 126        )
 127
 128        self._factory = factory_.Factory(self)
 129
 130    @property
 131    def factory(self) -> factory_.Factory:
 132        return self._factory
 133
 134    @property
 135    def rest(self) -> interfaces.RESTInterface:
 136        return self._rest
 137
 138    @property
 139    def request(self) -> Client:
 140        return copy.copy(self)
 141
 142    @property
 143    def metadata(self) -> collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any]:
 144        return self._rest.metadata
 145
 146    def run(
 147        self, future: collections.Coroutine[typing.Any, None, None], debug: bool = False
 148    ) -> None:
 149        loop: typing.Final[asyncio.AbstractEventLoop] = helpers.get_or_make_loop()
 150        try:
 151            if not loop.is_running():
 152                loop.set_debug(debug)
 153                loop.run_until_complete(future)
 154
 155        except Exception as exc:
 156            raise RuntimeError(f"Failed to run {future.__qualname__}") from exc
 157
 158        except KeyboardInterrupt:
 159            _LOG.warn("Unexpected Keyboard interrupt. Exiting.")
 160            return
 161
 162        finally:
 163            if self._rest.is_alive:
 164                # Clean up sessions.
 165                loop.run_until_complete(self._rest.close())
 166

 169    async def fetch_current_user_memberships(self, access_token: str, /) -> user.User:
 170        """Fetch and return a user object of the bungie net user associated with account.
 171
 172        .. warning::
 173            This method requires OAuth2 scope and a Bearer access token.
 174
 175        Parameters
 176        ----------
 177        access_token : `str`
 178            A valid Bearer access token for the authorization.
 179
 180        Returns
 181        -------
 182        `aiobungie.crate.user.User`
 183            A user object includes the Destiny memberships and Bungie.net user.
 184        """
 185        resp = await self.rest.fetch_current_user_memberships(access_token)
 186        assert isinstance(resp, dict)
 187        return self.factory.deserialize_user(resp)

 215    async def search_users(
 216        self, name: str, /
 217    ) -> iterators.FlatIterator[user.SearchableDestinyUser]:
 218        """Search for players and return all players that matches the same name.
 219
 220        Parameters
 221        ----------

 224
 225        Returns

 314        """

 316        assert isinstance(payload, dict)
 317        return self.factory.deserialize_user(payload)

 542        *,
 543        membership_type: typedefs.IntAnd[
 544            enums.MembershipType
 545        ] = enums.MembershipType.ALL,
 546        page: int = 0,
 547        limit: int = 250,
 548    ) -> iterators.FlatIterator[activity.Activity]:
 549        """Fetch a Destiny 2 activity for the specified character id.
 550
 551        Parameters
 552        ----------
 553        member_id: `int`
 554            The user id that starts with `4611`.
 555        character_id: `int`
 556            The id of the character to retrieve the activities for.
 557        mode: `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.internal.enums.GameMode]`
 558            This parameter filters the game mode, Nightfall, Strike, Iron Banner, etc.
 559
 560        Other Parameters
 561        ----------------
 562        membership_type: `aiobungie.internal.enums.MembershipType`
 563            The Member ship type, if nothing was passed than it will return all.
 564        page: int
 565            The page number. Default is `0`
 566        limit: int
 567            Limit the returned result. Default is `250`.
 568
 569        Returns
 570        -------
 571        `aiobungie.iterators.FlatIterator[aiobungie.crate.Activity]`
 572            An iterator of the player's activities.
 573
 574        Raises
 575        ------
 576        `aiobungie.MembershipTypeError`
 577            The provided membership type was invalid.
 578        """
 579        resp = await self.rest.fetch_activities(
 580            member_id,
 581            character_id,
 582            mode,
 583            membership_type=membership_type,
 584            page=page,
 585            limit=limit,
 586        )
 587        assert isinstance(resp, dict)
 588        return self.factory.deserialize_activities(resp)
 589

 591        """Fetch a post activity details.
 592
 593        Parameters

 597
 598        Returns

 701        Raises

 704            The clan was not found.
 705        """

 707        assert isinstance(resp, dict)
 708        return self.factory.deserialize_clan(resp)

 752    async def fetch_groups_for_member(
 753        self,
 754        member_id: int,
 755        member_type: typedefs.IntAnd[enums.MembershipType],
 756        /,
 757        *,
 758        filter: int = 0,
 759        group_type: enums.GroupType = enums.GroupType.CLAN,
 760    ) -> collections.Sequence[clans.GroupMember]:
 761        """Fetch information about the groups that a given member has joined.
 762
 763        Parameters
 764        ----------
 765        member_id : `int`
 766            The member's id
 767        member_type : `aiobungie.MembershipType`
 768            The member's membership type.
 769
 770        Other Parameters
 771        ----------------
 772        filter : `int`
 773            Filter apply to list of joined groups. This Default to `0`
 774        group_type : `aiobungie.GroupType`
 775            The group's type.
 776            This is always set to `aiobungie.GroupType.CLAN` and should not be changed.
 777
 778        Returns
 779        -------
 780        `collections.Sequence[aiobungie.crate.GroupMember]`
 781            A sequence of joined groups for the fetched member.
 782        """
 783        resp = await self.rest.fetch_groups_for_member(
 784            member_id, member_type, filter=filter, group_type=group_type
 785        )
 786        assert isinstance(resp, dict)
 787        return [
 788            self.factory.deserialize_group_member(group) for group in resp["results"]
 789        ]

1003    async def fetch_fireteams(
1004        self,
1005        activity_type: typedefs.IntAnd[fireteams.FireteamActivity],
1006        *,
1007        platform: typedefs.IntAnd[
1008            fireteams.FireteamPlatform
1009        ] = fireteams.FireteamPlatform.ANY,
1010        language: typing.Union[
1011            fireteams.FireteamLanguage, str
1012        ] = fireteams.FireteamLanguage.ALL,
1013        date_range: int = 0,
1014        page: int = 0,
1015        slots_filter: int = 0,
1016    ) -> typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[fireteams.Fireteam]]:
1017        """Fetch public Bungie fireteams with open slots.
1018
1019        Parameters
1020        ----------
1021        activity_type : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.crate.FireteamActivity]`
1022            The fireteam activity type.
1023
1024        Other Parameters
1025        ----------------
1026        platform : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.crate.fireteams.FireteamPlatform]`
1027            If this is provided. Then the results will be filtered with the given platform.
1028            Defaults to `aiobungie.crate.FireteamPlatform.ANY` which returns all platforms.
1029        language : `typing.Union[aiobungie.crate.fireteams.FireteamLanguage, str]`
1030            A locale language to filter the used language in that fireteam.
1031            Defaults to `aiobungie.crate.FireteamLanguage.ALL`
1032        date_range : `int`
1033            An integer to filter the date range of the returned fireteams. Defaults to `aiobungie.FireteamDate.ALL`.
1034        page : `int`
1035            The page number. By default its `0` which returns all available activities.
1036        slots_filter : `int`
1037            Filter the returned fireteams based on available slots. Default is `0`
1038
1039        Returns
1040        -------
1041        `typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[fireteams.Fireteam]]`
1042            A sequence of `aiobungie.crate.Fireteam` or `None`.
1043        """
1044
1045        resp = await self.rest.fetch_fireteams(
1046            activity_type,
1047            platform=platform,
1048            language=language,
1049            date_range=date_range,
1050            page=page,
1051            slots_filter=slots_filter,
1052        )
1053        assert isinstance(resp, dict)
1054        return self.factory.deserialize_fireteams(resp)
1055
1056    async def fetch_avaliable_clan_fireteams(
1057        self,
1058        access_token: str,
1059        group_id: int,
1060        activity_type: typedefs.IntAnd[fireteams.FireteamActivity],
1061        *,
1062        platform: typedefs.IntAnd[fireteams.FireteamPlatform],
1063        language: typing.Union[fireteams.FireteamLanguage, str],
1064        date_range: int = 0,
1065        page: int = 0,
1066        public_only: bool = False,
1067        slots_filter: int = 0,
1068    ) -> typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[fireteams.Fireteam]]:
1069        """Fetch a clan's fireteams with open slots.
1070
1071        .. note::
1072            This method requires OAuth2: ReadGroups scope.
1073
1074        Parameters
1075        ----------
1076        access_token : `str`
1077            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
1078        group_id : `int`
1079            The group/clan id of the fireteam.
1080        activity_type : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.crate.FireteamActivity]`
1081            The fireteam activity type.
1082
1083        Other Parameters
1084        ----------------
1085        platform : `aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.crate.fireteams.FireteamPlatform]`
1086            If this is provided. Then the results will be filtered with the given platform.
1087            Defaults to `aiobungie.crate.FireteamPlatform.ANY` which returns all platforms.
1088        language : `typing.Union[aiobungie.crate.fireteams.FireteamLanguage, str]`
1089            A locale language to filter the used language in that fireteam.
1090            Defaults to `aiobungie.crate.FireteamLanguage.ALL`
1091        date_range : `int`
1092            An integer to filter the date range of the returned fireteams. Defaults to `0`.
1093        page : `int`
1094            The page number. By default its `0` which returns all available activities.
1095        public_only: `bool`
1096            If set to True, Then only public fireteams will be returned.
1097        slots_filter : `int`
1098            Filter the returned fireteams based on available slots. Default is `0`
1099
1100        Returns
1101        -------
1102        `typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[aiobungie.crate.Fireteam]]`
1103            A sequence of  fireteams found in the clan.
1104            `None` will be returned if nothing was found.
1105        """
1106        resp = await self.rest.fetch_avaliable_clan_fireteams(
1107            access_token,
1108            group_id,
1109            activity_type,
1110            platform=platform,
1111            language=language,
1112            date_range=date_range,
1113            page=page,
1114            public_only=public_only,
1115            slots_filter=slots_filter,
1116        )
1117        assert isinstance(resp, dict)
1118        return self.factory.deserialize_fireteams(resp)

1120    async def fetch_clan_fireteam(
1121        self, access_token: str, fireteam_id: int, group_id: int
1122    ) -> fireteams.AvailableFireteam:
1123        """Fetch a specific clan fireteam.
1124
1125        .. note::
1126            This method requires OAuth2: ReadGroups scope.
1127
1128        Parameters
1129        ----------
1130        access_token : `str`
1131            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
1132        group_id : `int`
1133            The group/clan id to fetch the fireteam from.
1134        fireteam_id : `int`
1135            The fireteam id to fetch.
1136
1137        Returns
1138        -------
1139        `typing.Optional[aiobungie.crate.AvailableFireteam]`
1140            A sequence of available fireteams objects if exists. else `None` will be returned.
1141        """
1142        resp = await self.rest.fetch_clan_fireteam(access_token, fireteam_id, group_id)
1143        assert isinstance(resp, dict)
1144        return self.factory.deserialize_available_fireteams(
1145            resp, no_results=True
1146        )  # type: ignore[return-value]

1148    async def fetch_my_clan_fireteams(
1149        self,
1150        access_token: str,
1151        group_id: int,
1152        *,
1153        include_closed: bool = True,
1154        platform: typedefs.IntAnd[fireteams.FireteamPlatform],
1155        language: typing.Union[fireteams.FireteamLanguage, str],
1156        filtered: bool = True,
1157        page: int = 0,
1158    ) -> collections.Sequence[fireteams.AvailableFireteam]:
1159        """A method that's similar to `fetch_fireteams` but requires OAuth2.
1160
1161        .. note::
1162            This method requires OAuth2: ReadGroups scope.
1163
1164        Parameters
1165        ----------
1166        access_token : str
1167            The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
1168        group_id : int
1169            The group/clan id to fetch.
1170
1171        Other Parameters
1172        ----------------
1173        include_closed : bool
1174            If provided and set to True, It will also return closed fireteams.
1175            If provided and set to False, It will only return public fireteams. Default is True.
1176        platform : aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.crate.fireteams.FireteamPlatform]
1177            If this is provided. Then the results will be filtered with the given platform.
1178            Defaults to aiobungie.crate.FireteamPlatform.ANY which returns all platforms.
1179        language : typing.Union[aiobungie.crate.fireteams.FireteamLanguage, str]
1180            A locale language to filter the used language in that fireteam.
1181            Defaults to aiobungie.crate.FireteamLanguage.ALL
1182        filtered : bool
1183            If set to True, it will filter by clan. Otherwise not. Default is True.
1184        page : int
1185            The page number. By default its 0 which returns all available activities.
1186
1187        Returns
1188        -------
1189        `collections.Sequence[aiobungie.crate.AvailableFireteam]`
1190            A sequence of available fireteams objects if exists. else `None` will be returned.
1191        """
1192        resp = await self.rest.fetch_my_clan_fireteams(
1193            access_token,
1194            group_id,
1195            include_closed=include_closed,
1196            platform=platform,
1197            language=language,
1198            filtered=filtered,
1199            page=page,
1200        )
1201        assert isinstance(resp, dict)
1202        return self.factory.deserialize_available_fireteams(resp)  # type: ignore[return-value]

Standard Bungie API client application.

This client deserialize the REST JSON responses using aiobungie.Factory and returns aiobungie.crate Python object implementations of the responses.

A aiobungie.RESTClient REST client can also be used alone for low-level concepts.

Parameters
  • token (str): Your Bungie's API key or Token from the developer's portal.
Other Parameters
  • rest_client (aiobungie.interfaces.RESTInterface | None): An optional rest client instance you can pass. If set to None then the client will use the default instance.
Example
TOKEN = "SOME_TOKEN"
async with aiobungie.RESTClient(TOKEN, max_retries=2) as rest_client:
    client = aiobungie.Client(TOKEN, rest_client=rest_client)

max_retries : int The max retries number to retry if the request hit a 5xx status code. max_ratelimit_retries : int The max retries number to retry if the request hit a 429 status code. Defaults to 3. client_secret : str | None An optional application client secret, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client. client_id : int | None An optional application client id, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.

#   Client( token: str, /, client_secret: Optional[str] = None, client_id: Optional[int] = None, *, rest_client: Optional[aiobungie.interfaces.rest.RESTInterface] = None, max_retries: int = 4, max_ratelimit_retries: int = 3 )

#   def run( self, future: collections.abc.Coroutine[typing.Any, None, None], debug: bool = False ) -> None:
View Source 
146    def run(
147        self, future: collections.Coroutine[typing.Any, None, None], debug: bool = False
148    ) -> None:
149        loop: typing.Final[asyncio.AbstractEventLoop] = helpers.get_or_make_loop()
150        try:
151            if not loop.is_running():
152                loop.set_debug(debug)
153                loop.run_until_complete(future)
154
155        except Exception as exc:
156            raise RuntimeError(f"Failed to run {future.__qualname__}") from exc
157
158        except KeyboardInterrupt:
159            _LOG.warn("Unexpected Keyboard interrupt. Exiting.")
160            return
161
162        finally:
163            if self._rest.is_alive:
164                # Clean up sessions.
165                loop.run_until_complete(self._rest.close())

Runs a coroutine function until its complete.

This is equivalent to asyncio.get_event_loop().run_until_complete(...)

Parameters
  • future (collections.Coroutine[None, None, None]): A coroutine object.
  • debug (bool): Either to enable asyncio debug or not. Disabled by default.
Example
async def main() -> None:
    await fetch(...)

# Run the coroutine.
client.run(main())

#   class Enum(enum.Enum):

76class Enum(__enum.Enum):
77    """Builtin Python enum with extra handlings."""
78
79    @property
80    def name(self) -> str:  # type: ignore[override]
81        return self._name_
82
83    @property
84    def value(self) -> typing.Any:  # type: ignore[override]
85        return self._value_
86
87    def __str__(self) -> str:
88        return self._name_
89
90    def __repr__(self) -> str:
91        return f"<{type(self).__name__}.{self._name_}: {self._value_!s}>"
92
93    def __int__(self) -> int:
94        if isinstance(self.value, _ITERABLE):
95            raise TypeError(
96                f"Can't overload {self.value} in {type(self).__name__}, Please use `.value` attribute.",
97            )
98        return int(self.value)

Builtin Python enum with extra handlings.

  61class Factory(interfaces.FactoryInterface):
  62    """The base deserialization factory class for all aiobungie objects.
  63
  64    Highly inspired hikari entity factory used to deserialize JSON responses from the REST client and turning them
  65    into a `aiobungie.crate` Python classes.
  66    """
  67
  68    __slots__ = ("_net",)
  69
  70    def __init__(self, net: traits.Netrunner) -> None:
  71        self._net = net
  72
  73    def deserialize_bungie_user(self, data: typedefs.JSONObject) -> user.BungieUser:
  74        return user.BungieUser(
  75            id=int(data["membershipId"]),
  76            created_at=time.clean_date(data["firstAccess"]),
  77            name=data.get("cachedBungieGlobalDisplayName", undefined.Undefined),
  78            is_deleted=data["isDeleted"],
  79            about=data["about"],
  80            updated_at=time.clean_date(data["lastUpdate"]),
  81            psn_name=data.get("psnDisplayName", None),
  82            stadia_name=data.get("stadiaDisplayName", None),
  83            steam_name=data.get("steamDisplayName", None),
  84            twitch_name=data.get("twitchDisplayName", None),
  85            blizzard_name=data.get("blizzardDisplayName", None),
  86            status=data["statusText"],
  87            locale=data["locale"],
  88            picture=assets.Image(path=str(data["profilePicturePath"])),
  89            code=data.get("cachedBungieGlobalDisplayNameCode", None),
  90            unique_name=data.get("uniqueName", None),
  91            theme_id=int(data["profileTheme"]),
  92            show_activity=bool(data["showActivity"]),
  93            theme_name=data["profileThemeName"],
  94            display_title=data["userTitleDisplay"],
  95        )
  96
  97    def deserialize_partial_bungie_user(
  98        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
  99    ) -> user.PartialBungieUser:
 100        return user.PartialBungieUser(
 101            net=self._net,
 102            types=[
 103                enums.MembershipType(type_)
 104                for type_ in payload.get("applicableMembershipTypes", [])
 105            ],
 106            name=payload.get("displayName", undefined.Undefined),
 107            id=int(payload["membershipId"]),
 108            crossave_override=enums.MembershipType(payload["crossSaveOverride"]),
 109            is_public=payload["isPublic"],
 110            icon=assets.Image(payload.get("iconPath", "")),
 111            type=enums.MembershipType(payload["membershipType"]),
 112        )

 114    def deserialize_destiny_membership(
 115        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 116    ) -> user.DestinyMembership:
 117        name: undefined.UndefinedOr[str] = undefined.Undefined
 118        if (
 119            raw_name := payload.get("bungieGlobalDisplayName", "")
 120        ) and not typedefs.is_unknown(raw_name):
 121            name = raw_name
 122
 123        return user.DestinyMembership(
 124            net=self._net,
 125            id=int(payload["membershipId"]),
 126            name=name,
 127            code=payload.get("bungieGlobalDisplayNameCode", None),
 128            last_seen_name=payload.get("LastSeenDisplayName", payload["displayName"]),
 129            type=enums.MembershipType(payload["membershipType"]),
 130            is_public=payload["isPublic"],
 131            crossave_override=enums.MembershipType(payload["crossSaveOverride"]),
 132            icon=assets.Image(payload.get("iconPath", "")),
 133            types=[
 134                enums.MembershipType(type_)
 135                for type_ in payload["applicableMembershipTypes"]
 136            ],
 137        )

 139    def deserialize_destiny_memberships(
 140        self, data: typedefs.JSONArray
 141    ) -> collections.Sequence[user.DestinyMembership]:
 142        return [self.deserialize_destiny_membership(membership) for membership in data]

 144    def deserialize_user(self, data: typedefs.JSONObject) -> user.User:
 145
 146        primary_membership_id: typing.Optional[int] = None
 147        if raw_primary_id := data.get("primaryMembershipId"):
 148            primary_membership_id = int(raw_primary_id)
 149
 150        return user.User(
 151            bungie=self.deserialize_bungie_user(data["bungieNetUser"]),
 152            destiny=self.deserialize_destiny_memberships(data["destinyMemberships"]),
 153            primary_membership_id=primary_membership_id,
 154        )

 156    def deserialize_searched_user(
 157        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 158    ) -> user.SearchableDestinyUser:
 159        name: undefined.UndefinedOr[str] = undefined.Undefined
 160        if (raw_name := payload["bungieGlobalDisplayName"]) and not typedefs.is_unknown(
 161            raw_name
 162        ):
 163            name = raw_name
 164
 165        code: typing.Optional[int] = None
 166        if raw_code := payload.get("bungieGlobalDisplayNameCode"):
 167            code = int(raw_code)
 168
 169        bungie_id: typing.Optional[int] = None
 170        if raw_bungie_id := payload.get("bungieNetMembershipId"):
 171            bungie_id = int(raw_bungie_id)
 172
 173        return user.SearchableDestinyUser(
 174            name=name,
 175            code=code,
 176            bungie_id=bungie_id,
 177            memberships=self.deserialize_destiny_memberships(
 178                payload["destinyMemberships"]
 179            ),
 180        )

 191            )
 192            for creds in payload
 193        ]

 195    @staticmethod
 196    def set_themese_attrs(
 197        payload: typedefs.JSONArray, /
 198    ) -> typing.Collection[user.UserThemes]:
 199
 200        theme_map: dict[int, user.UserThemes] = {}
 201        theme_ids: list[int] = helpers.just(payload, "userThemeId")
 202        theme_names: list[typedefs.NoneOr[str]] = helpers.just(payload, "userThemeName")
 203        theme_descriptions: list[typedefs.NoneOr[str]] = helpers.just(
 204            payload, "userThemeDescription"
 205        )
 206
 207        for t_id, t_name, t_desc in zip(theme_ids, theme_names, theme_descriptions):
 208            theme_map[t_id] = user.UserThemes(
 209                id=int(t_id),
 210                name=t_name or undefined.Undefined,
 211                description=t_desc or undefined.Undefined,
 212            )
 213        return theme_map.values()

 215    def deserialize_user_themes(
 216        self, payload: typedefs.JSONArray
 217    ) -> collections.Sequence[user.UserThemes]:
 218        return list(self.set_themese_attrs(payload))

 220    def deserialize_clan(self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject) -> clans.Clan:
 221
 222        # This is kinda redundant
 223        data = payload
 224
 225        # This is always outside the details.
 226        current_user_map: typing.Optional[
 227            collections.Mapping[str, clans.ClanMember]
 228        ] = None
 229        if raw_current_user_map := payload.get("currentUserMemberMap"):
 230            current_user_map = {
 231                membership_type: self.deserialize_clan_member(membership)
 232                for membership_type, membership in raw_current_user_map.items()
 233            }
 234
 235        try:
 236            data = payload["detail"]
 237        except KeyError:
 238            pass
 239
 240        id = data["groupId"]
 241        name = data["name"]
 242        created_at = data["creationDate"]
 243        member_count = data["memberCount"]
 244        about = data["about"]
 245        motto = data["motto"]
 246        is_public = data["isPublic"]
 247        banner = assets.Image(str(data["bannerPath"]))
 248        avatar = assets.Image(str(data["avatarPath"]))
 249        tags = data["tags"]
 250        type = data["groupType"]
 251
 252        features = data["features"]
 253        features_obj = clans.ClanFeatures(
 254            max_members=features["maximumMembers"],
 255            max_membership_types=features["maximumMembershipsOfGroupType"],
 256            capabilities=features["capabilities"],
 257            membership_types=features["membershipTypes"],
 258            invite_permissions=features["invitePermissionOverride"],
 259            update_banner_permissions=features["updateBannerPermissionOverride"],
 260            update_culture_permissions=features["updateCulturePermissionOverride"],
 261            join_level=features["joinLevel"],
 262        )
 263
 264        information: typedefs.JSONObject = data["clanInfo"]
 265        progression: collections.Mapping[int, progressions.Progression] = {
 266            int(prog_hash): self.deserialize_progressions(prog)
 267            for prog_hash, prog in information["d2ClanProgressions"].items()
 268        }
 269
 270        founder: typedefs.NoneOr[clans.ClanMember] = None
 271        if raw_founder := payload.get("founder"):
 272            founder = self.deserialize_clan_member(raw_founder)
 273
 274        return clans.Clan(
 275            net=self._net,
 276            id=int(id),
 277            name=name,
 278            type=enums.GroupType(type),
 279            created_at=time.clean_date(created_at),
 280            member_count=member_count,
 281            motto=motto,
 282            about=about,
 283            is_public=is_public,
 284            banner=banner,
 285            avatar=avatar,
 286            tags=tags,
 287            features=features_obj,
 288            owner=founder,
 289            progressions=progression,
 290            call_sign=information["clanCallsign"],
 291            banner_data=information["clanBannerData"],
 292            chat_security=data["chatSecurity"],
 293            conversation_id=int(data["conversationId"]),
 294            allow_chat=data["allowChat"],
 295            theme=data["theme"],
 296            current_user_membership=current_user_map,
 297        )
 298
 299    def deserialize_clan_member(self, data: typedefs.JSONObject, /) -> clans.ClanMember:
 300        destiny_user = self.deserialize_destiny_membership(data["destinyUserInfo"])
 301        return clans.ClanMember(
 302            net=self._net,
 303            last_seen_name=destiny_user.last_seen_name,
 304            id=destiny_user.id,
 305            name=destiny_user.name,
 306            icon=destiny_user.icon,
 307            last_online=time.from_timestamp(int(data["lastOnlineStatusChange"])),
 308            group_id=int(data["groupId"]),
 309            joined_at=time.clean_date(data["joinDate"]),
 310            types=destiny_user.types,
 311            is_public=destiny_user.is_public,
 312            type=destiny_user.type,
 313            code=destiny_user.code,
 314            is_online=data["isOnline"],
 315            crossave_override=destiny_user.crossave_override,
 316            bungie=self.deserialize_partial_bungie_user(data["bungieNetUserInfo"])
 317            if "bungieNetUserInfo" in data
 318            else None,
 319            member_type=enums.ClanMemberType(int(data["memberType"])),
 320        )

 322    def deserialize_clan_members(
 323        self, data: typedefs.JSONObject, /
 324    ) -> iterators.FlatIterator[clans.ClanMember]:
 325        return iterators.FlatIterator(
 326            [self.deserialize_clan_member(member) for member in data["results"]]

 329    def deserialize_group_member(
 330        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 331    ) -> clans.GroupMember:
 332        member = payload["member"]
 333        return clans.GroupMember(
 334            net=self._net,
 335            join_date=time.clean_date(member["joinDate"]),
 336            group_id=int(member["groupId"]),
 337            member_type=enums.ClanMemberType(member["memberType"]),
 338            is_online=member["isOnline"],
 339            last_online=time.from_timestamp(int(member["lastOnlineStatusChange"])),
 340            inactive_memberships=payload.get("areAllMembershipsInactive", None),
 341            member=self.deserialize_destiny_membership(member["destinyUserInfo"]),
 342            group=self.deserialize_clan(payload["group"]),
 343        )

 345    def deserialize_clan_conversations(
 346        self, payload: typedefs.JSONArray
 347    ) -> collections.Sequence[clans.ClanConversation]:
 348        map = {}
 349        vec: list[clans.ClanConversation] = []
 350        if payload:
 351            for convo in payload:
 352                for k, v in convo.items():
 353                    map[k] = v
 354
 355                name: undefined.UndefinedOr[str] = undefined.Undefined
 356                if (raw_name := map["chatName"]) and not typedefs.is_unknown(raw_name):
 357                    name = raw_name
 358
 359                convo_obj = clans.ClanConversation(
 360                    net=self._net,
 361                    group_id=int(map["groupId"]),
 362                    id=int(map["conversationId"]),
 363                    chat_enabled=map["chatEnabled"],
 364                    name=name,
 365                    security=map["chatSecurity"],
 366                )
 367                vec.append(convo_obj)
 368        return vec

 396    def _set_character_attrs(self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject) -> character.Character:
 397        total_time = time.format_played(int(payload["minutesPlayedTotal"]), suffix=True)
 398        return character.Character(
 399            net=self._net,
 400            id=int(payload["characterId"]),
 401            gender=enums.Gender(payload["genderType"]),

 404            emblem=assets.Image(str(payload["emblemBackgroundPath"])),
 405            emblem_icon=assets.Image(str(payload["emblemPath"])),
 406            emblem_hash=int(payload["emblemHash"]),
 407            last_played=time.clean_date(payload["dateLastPlayed"]),
 408            total_played_time=total_time,
 409            member_id=int(payload["membershipId"]),
 410            member_type=enums.MembershipType(payload["membershipType"]),
 411            level=payload["baseCharacterLevel"],
 412            title_hash=payload.get("titleRecordHash", None),

 417    def deserialize_profile(
 418        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject, /
 419    ) -> typing.Optional[profile.Profile]:
 420        if (raw_profile := payload.get("data")) is None:
 421            return None
 422
 423        payload = raw_profile
 424        id = int(payload["userInfo"]["membershipId"])
 425        name = payload["userInfo"]["displayName"]
 426        is_public = payload["userInfo"]["isPublic"]
 427        type = enums.MembershipType(payload["userInfo"]["membershipType"])
 428        last_played = time.clean_date(str(payload["dateLastPlayed"]))
 429        character_ids = [int(cid) for cid in payload["characterIds"]]
 430        power_cap = payload["currentSeasonRewardPowerCap"]
 431
 432        return profile.Profile(
 433            id=int(id),
 434            name=name,
 435            is_public=is_public,
 436            type=type,
 437            last_played=last_played,
 438            character_ids=character_ids,
 439            power_cap=power_cap,
 440            net=self._net,
 441        )

 443    def deserialize_profile_item(
 444        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 445    ) -> profile.ProfileItemImpl:
 446
 447        instance_id: typing.Optional[int] = None
 448        if raw_instance_id := payload.get("itemInstanceId"):
 449            instance_id = int(raw_instance_id)
 450
 451        version_number: typing.Optional[int] = None
 452        if raw_version := payload.get("versionNumber"):
 453            version_number = int(raw_version)
 454
 455        transfer_status = enums.TransferStatus(payload["transferStatus"])
 456
 457        return profile.ProfileItemImpl(
 458            net=self._net,
 459            hash=payload["itemHash"],
 460            quantity=payload["quantity"],
 461            bind_status=enums.ItemBindStatus(payload["bindStatus"]),
 462            location=enums.ItemLocation(payload["location"]),
 463            bucket=payload["bucketHash"],
 464            transfer_status=transfer_status,
 465            lockable=payload["lockable"],
 466            state=enums.ItemState(payload["state"]),
 467            dismantel_permissions=payload["dismantlePermission"],
 468            is_wrapper=payload["isWrapper"],
 469            instance_id=instance_id,
 470            version_number=version_number,
 471            ornament_id=payload.get("overrideStyleItemHash"),
 472        )
 473
 474    def deserialize_objectives(self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject) -> records.Objective:
 475        return records.Objective(
 476            net=self._net,
 477            hash=payload["objectiveHash"],
 478            visible=payload["visible"],
 479            complete=payload["complete"],
 480            completion_value=payload["completionValue"],
 481            progress=payload.get("progress"),
 482            destination_hash=payload.get("destinationHash"),
 483            activity_hash=payload.get("activityHash"),
 484        )
 485
 486    def deserialize_records(
 487        self,
 488        payload: typedefs.JSONObject,
 489        scores: typing.Optional[records.RecordScores] = None,
 490        **nodes: int,
 491    ) -> records.Record:
 492        objectives: typing.Optional[list[records.Objective]] = None
 493        interval_objectives: typing.Optional[list[records.Objective]] = None
 494        record_state: typedefs.IntAnd[records.RecordState]
 495
 496        record_state = records.RecordState(payload["state"])
 497
 498        if raw_objs := payload.get("objectives"):
 499            objectives = [self.deserialize_objectives(obj) for obj in raw_objs]
 500
 501        if raw_interval_objs := payload.get("intervalObjectives"):
 502            interval_objectives = [
 503                self.deserialize_objectives(obj) for obj in raw_interval_objs
 504            ]
 505
 506        return records.Record(
 507            scores=scores,
 508            categories_node_hash=nodes.get("categories_hash", undefined.Undefined),
 509            seals_node_hash=nodes.get("seals_hash", undefined.Undefined),
 510            state=record_state,
 511            objectives=objectives,
 512            interval_objectives=interval_objectives,
 513            redeemed_count=payload.get("intervalsRedeemedCount", 0),
 514            completion_times=payload.get("completedCount", None),
 515            reward_visibility=payload.get("rewardVisibilty", None),
 516        )
 517
 518    def deserialize_character_records(
 519        self,
 520        payload: typedefs.JSONObject,
 521        scores: typing.Optional[records.RecordScores] = None,
 522        record_hashes: typing.Optional[list[int]] = None,
 523    ) -> records.CharacterRecord:
 524
 525        record = self.deserialize_records(payload, scores)
 526        return records.CharacterRecord(
 527            scores=scores,
 528            categories_node_hash=record.categories_node_hash,
 529            seals_node_hash=record.seals_node_hash,
 530            state=record.state,
 531            objectives=record.objectives,
 532            interval_objectives=record.interval_objectives,
 533            redeemed_count=payload.get("intervalsRedeemedCount", 0),
 534            completion_times=payload.get("completedCount"),
 535            reward_visibility=payload.get("rewardVisibilty"),
 536            record_hashes=record_hashes or [],
 537        )

 607    def deserialize_character_activity(
 608        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 609    ) -> activity.CharacterActivity:
 610        current_mode: typing.Optional[enums.GameMode] = None
 611        if raw_current_mode := payload.get("currentActivityModeType"):
 612            current_mode = enums.GameMode(raw_current_mode)
 613
 614        current_mode_types: typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[enums.GameMode]] = None
 615        if raw_current_modes := payload.get("currentActivityModeTypes"):
 616            current_mode_types = [enums.GameMode(type_) for type_ in raw_current_modes]
 617
 618        return activity.CharacterActivity(
 619            date_started=time.clean_date(payload["dateActivityStarted"]),
 620            current_hash=payload["currentActivityHash"],
 621            current_mode_hash=payload["currentActivityModeHash"],
 622            current_mode=current_mode,
 623            current_mode_hashes=payload.get("currentActivityModeHashes"),
 624            current_mode_types=current_mode_types,
 625            current_playlist_hash=payload.get("currentPlaylistActivityHash"),
 626            last_story_hash=payload["lastCompletedStoryHash"],
 627            available_activities=[
 628                self.deserialize_available_activity(activity_)
 629                for activity_ in payload["availableActivities"]
 630            ],
 631        )

 638    def _deserialize_node(self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject) -> records.Node:
 639        return records.Node(
 640            state=int(payload["state"]),
 641            objective=self.deserialize_objectives(payload["objective"])
 642            if "objective" in payload
 643            else None,
 644            progress_value=int(payload["progressValue"]),
 645            completion_value=int(payload["completionValue"]),
 646            record_category_score=int(payload["recordCategoryScore"])
 647            if "recordCategoryScore" in payload
 648            else None,
 649        )

 651    @staticmethod
 652    def _deserialize_collectible(payload: typedefs.JSONObject) -> items.Collectible:
 653        recent_collectibles: typing.Optional[collections.Collection[int]] = None
 654        if raw_recent_collectibles := payload.get("recentCollectibleHashes"):
 655            recent_collectibles = [
 656                int(item_hash) for item_hash in raw_recent_collectibles
 657            ]
 658
 659        collectibles: dict[int, int] = {}
 660        for item_hash, mapping in payload["collectibles"].items():
 661            collectibles[int(item_hash)] = int(mapping["state"])
 662
 663        return items.Collectible(
 664            recent_collectibles=recent_collectibles,
 665            collectibles=collectibles,
 666            collection_categorie_hash=int(payload["collectionCategoriesRootNodeHash"]),
 667            collection_badges_hash=int(payload["collectionBadgesRootNodeHash"]),
 668        )

 673    ) -> collections.Sequence[items.Currency]:
 674        return [
 675            items.Currency(hash=int(item_hash), amount=int(amount))
 676            for item_hash, amount in payload["itemQuantities"].items()
 677        ]

 720    def _deserialize_milestone_activity(
 721        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 722    ) -> milestones.MilestoneActivity:
 723
 724        phases: typing.Optional[
 725            collections.Sequence[milestones.MilestoneActivityPhase]
 726        ] = None
 727        if raw_phases := payload.get("phases"):
 728            phases = [
 729                milestones.MilestoneActivityPhase(
 730                    is_completed=obj["complete"], hash=obj["phaseHash"]
 731                )
 732                for obj in raw_phases
 733            ]
 734
 735        return milestones.MilestoneActivity(
 736            hash=payload["activityHash"],
 737            challenges=[
 738                self.deserialize_objectives(obj["objective"])
 739                for obj in payload["challenges"]
 740            ],
 741            modifier_hashes=payload.get("modifierHashes"),
 742            boolean_options=payload.get("booleanActivityOptions"),
 743            phases=phases,
 744        )

 751            quest_hash=payload["questHash"],
 752            step_hash=payload["stepHash"],
 753            step_objectives=[
 754                self.deserialize_objectives(objective)
 755                for objective in payload["stepObjectives"]
 756            ],
 757            is_tracked=payload["tracked"],
 758            is_completed=payload["completed"],
 759            started=payload["started"],
 760            item_instance_id=payload["itemInstanceId"],
 761            vendor_hash=payload.get("vendorHash"),
 762            is_redeemed=payload["redeemed"],
 763        )

 766        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 767    ) -> milestones.MilestoneReward:
 768        return milestones.MilestoneReward(
 769            category_hash=payload["rewardCategoryHash"],
 770            entries=[
 771                milestones.MilestoneRewardEntry(
 772                    entry_hash=entry["rewardEntryHash"],
 773                    is_earned=entry["earned"],
 774                    is_redeemed=entry["redeemed"],
 775                )
 776                for entry in payload["entries"]
 777            ],
 778        )
 779
 780    def deserialize_milestone(
 781        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 782    ) -> milestones.Milestone:
 783        start_date: typing.Optional[datetime.datetime] = None
 784        if raw_start_date := payload.get("startDate"):
 785            start_date = time.clean_date(raw_start_date)
 786
 787        end_date: typing.Optional[datetime.datetime] = None
 788        if raw_end_date := payload.get("endDate"):
 789            end_date = time.clean_date(raw_end_date)
 790
 791        rewards: typing.Optional[
 792            collections.Collection[milestones.MilestoneReward]
 793        ] = None
 794        if raw_rewards := payload.get("rewards"):
 795            rewards = [
 796                self._deserialize_milestone_rewards(reward) for reward in raw_rewards
 797            ]
 798
 799        activities: typing.Optional[
 800            collections.Sequence[milestones.MilestoneActivity]
 801        ] = None
 802        if raw_activities := payload.get("activities"):
 803            activities = [
 804                self._deserialize_milestone_activity(active)
 805                for active in raw_activities
 806            ]
 807
 808        quests: typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[milestones.MilestoneQuest]] = None
 809        if raw_quests := payload.get("availableQuests"):
 810            quests = [
 811                self._deserialize_milestone_available_quest(quest)
 812                for quest in raw_quests
 813            ]
 814
 815        vendors: typing.Optional[
 816            collections.Sequence[milestones.MilestoneVendor]
 817        ] = None
 818        if raw_vendors := payload.get("vendors"):
 819            vendors = [
 820                milestones.MilestoneVendor(
 821                    vendor_hash=vendor["vendorHash"],
 822                    preview_itemhash=vendor.get("previewItemHash"),
 823                )
 824                for vendor in raw_vendors
 825            ]
 826
 827        return milestones.Milestone(
 828            hash=payload["milestoneHash"],
 829            start_date=start_date,
 830            end_date=end_date,
 831            order=payload["order"],
 832            rewards=rewards,
 833            available_quests=quests,
 834            activities=activities,
 835            vendors=vendors,
 836        )
 837

 846                season.ArtifactTierItem(
 847                    hash=item["itemHash"], is_active=item["isActive"]
 848                )
 849                for item in payload["items"]
 850            ],
 851        )

 890    def deserialize_character_progressions(
 891        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 892    ) -> character.CharacterProgression:
 893        progressions_ = {
 894            int(prog_id): self.deserialize_progressions(prog)
 895            for prog_id, prog in payload["progressions"].items()
 896        }
 897
 898        factions = {
 899            int(faction_id): self._deserialize_factions(faction)
 900            for faction_id, faction in payload["factions"].items()
 901        }
 902
 903        milestones_ = {
 904            int(milestone_hash): self.deserialize_milestone(milestone)
 905            for milestone_hash, milestone in payload["milestones"].items()
 906        }
 907
 908        uninstanced_item_objectives = {
 909            int(item_hash): [self.deserialize_objectives(ins) for ins in obj]
 910            for item_hash, obj in payload["uninstancedItemObjectives"].items()
 911        }
 912
 913        artifact = payload["seasonalArtifact"]
 914        seasonal_artifact = season.CharacterScopedArtifact(
 915            hash=artifact["artifactHash"],
 916            points_used=artifact["pointsUsed"],
 917            reset_count=artifact["resetCount"],
 918            tiers=[
 919                self._deserialize_artifact_tiers(tier) for tier in artifact["tiers"]
 920            ],
 921        )
 922        checklists = payload["checklists"]
 923
 924        return character.CharacterProgression(
 925            progressions=progressions_,
 926            factions=factions,
 927            checklists=checklists,
 928            milestones=milestones_,
 929            seasonal_artifact=seasonal_artifact,
 930            uninstanced_item_objectives=uninstanced_item_objectives,
 931        )
 932
 933    def deserialize_character_progressions_mapping(
 934        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 935    ) -> collections.Mapping[int, character.CharacterProgression]:
 936        character_progressions: collections.Mapping[
 937            int, character.CharacterProgression
 938        ] = {}
 939        for char_id, data in payload["data"].items():
 940            # A little hack to stop mypy complaining about Mapping <-> dict
 941            character_progressions[int(char_id)] = self.deserialize_character_progressions(data)  # type: ignore[index]
 942        return character_progressions
 943

 956    def deserialize_profile_records(
 957        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
 958    ) -> collections.Mapping[int, records.Record]:
 959        raw_profile_records = payload["data"]
 960        scores = records.RecordScores(
 961            current_score=raw_profile_records["score"],
 962            legacy_score=raw_profile_records["legacyScore"],
 963            lifetime_score=raw_profile_records["lifetimeScore"],
 964        )
 965        return {
 966            int(record_id): self.deserialize_records(
 967                record,
 968                scores,
 969                categories_hash=raw_profile_records["recordCategoriesRootNodeHash"],
 970                seals_hash=raw_profile_records["recordSealsRootNodeHash"],
 971            )
 972            for record_id, record in raw_profile_records["records"].items()
 973        }

1022
1023    def deserialize_components(  # noqa: C901 Too complex.
1024        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
1025    ) -> components.Component:
1026
1027        profile_: typing.Optional[profile.Profile] = None
1028        if raw_profile := payload.get("profile"):
1029            profile_ = self.deserialize_profile(raw_profile)
1030
1031        profile_progression: typing.Optional[profile.ProfileProgression] = None
1032        if raw_profile_progression := payload.get("profileProgression"):
1033            profile_progression = self.deserialize_profile_progression(
1034                raw_profile_progression
1035            )
1036
1037        profile_currencies: typing.Optional[
1038            collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]
1039        ] = None
1040        if raw_profile_currencies := payload.get("profileCurrencies"):
1041            if "data" in raw_profile_currencies:
1042                profile_currencies = self.deserialize_profile_items(
1043                    raw_profile_currencies["data"]
1044                )
1045
1046        profile_inventories: typing.Optional[
1047            collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]
1048        ] = None
1049        if raw_profile_inventories := payload.get("profileInventory"):
1050            if "data" in raw_profile_inventories:
1051                profile_inventories = self.deserialize_profile_items(
1052                    raw_profile_inventories["data"]
1053                )
1054
1055        profile_records: typing.Optional[
1056            collections.Mapping[int, records.Record]
1057        ] = None
1058
1059        if raw_profile_records_ := payload.get("profileRecords"):
1060            profile_records = self.deserialize_profile_records(raw_profile_records_)
1061
1062        characters: typing.Optional[typing.Mapping[int, character.Character]] = None
1063        if raw_characters := payload.get("characters"):
1064            characters = self.deserialize_characters(raw_characters)
1065
1066        character_records: typing.Optional[
1067            collections.Mapping[int, records.CharacterRecord]
1068        ] = None
1069
1070        if raw_character_records := payload.get("characterRecords"):
1071            # Had to do it in two steps..
1072            to_update: typedefs.JSONObject = {}
1073            for _, data in raw_character_records["data"].items():
1074                for record_id, record in data.items():
1075                    to_update[record_id] = record
1076
1077            character_records = {
1078                int(rec_id): self.deserialize_character_records(
1079                    rec, record_hashes=to_update.get("featuredRecordHashes")
1080                )
1081                for rec_id, rec in to_update["records"].items()
1082            }
1083
1084        character_equipments: typing.Optional[
1085            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]]
1086        ] = None
1087        if raw_character_equips := payload.get("characterEquipment"):
1088            character_equipments = self.deserialize_character_equipments(
1089                raw_character_equips
1090            )
1091
1092        character_inventories: typing.Optional[
1093            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]]
1094        ] = None
1095        if raw_character_inventories := payload.get("characterInventories"):
1096            if "data" in raw_character_inventories:
1097                character_inventories = self.deserialize_character_equipments(
1098                    raw_character_inventories
1099                )
1100
1101        character_activities: typing.Optional[
1102            collections.Mapping[int, activity.CharacterActivity]
1103        ] = None
1104        if raw_char_acts := payload.get("characterActivities"):
1105            character_activities = self.deserialize_character_activities(raw_char_acts)
1106
1107        character_render_data: typing.Optional[
1108            collections.Mapping[int, character.RenderedData]
1109        ] = None
1110        if raw_character_render_data := payload.get("characterRenderData"):
1111            character_render_data = self.deserialize_characters_render_data(
1112                raw_character_render_data
1113            )
1114
1115        character_progressions: typing.Optional[
1116            collections.Mapping[int, character.CharacterProgression]
1117        ] = None
1118
1119        if raw_character_progressions := payload.get("characterProgressions"):
1120            character_progressions = self.deserialize_character_progressions_mapping(
1121                raw_character_progressions
1122            )
1123
1124        profile_string_vars: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, int]] = None
1125        if raw_profile_string_vars := payload.get("profileStringVariables"):
1126            profile_string_vars = raw_profile_string_vars["data"]["integerValuesByHash"]
1127
1128        character_string_vars: typing.Optional[
1129            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Mapping[int, int]]
1130        ] = None
1131        if raw_character_string_vars := payload.get("characterStringVariables"):
1132            character_string_vars = {
1133                int(char_id): data["integerValuesByHash"]
1134                for char_id, data in raw_character_string_vars["data"].items()
1135            }
1136
1137        metrics: typing.Optional[
1138            collections.Sequence[
1139                collections.Mapping[
1140                    int, tuple[bool, typing.Optional[records.Objective]]
1141                ]
1142            ]
1143        ] = None
1144        root_node_hash: typing.Optional[int] = None
1145
1146        if raw_metrics := payload.get("metrics"):
1147            root_node_hash = raw_metrics["data"]["metricsRootNodeHash"]
1148            metrics = [
1149                {
1150                    int(metrics_hash): (
1151                        data["invisible"],
1152                        self.deserialize_objectives(data["objectiveProgress"])
1153                        if "objectiveProgress" in data
1154                        else None,
1155                    )
1156                    for metrics_hash, data in raw_metrics["data"]["metrics"].items()
1157                }
1158            ]
1159        transitory: typing.Optional[fireteams.FireteamParty] = None
1160        if raw_transitory := payload.get("profileTransitoryData"):
1161            if "data" in raw_transitory:
1162                transitory = self.deserialize_fireteam_party(raw_transitory["data"])
1163
1164        item_components: typing.Optional[components.ItemsComponent] = None
1165        if raw_item_components := payload.get("itemComponents"):
1166            item_components = self.deserialize_items_component(raw_item_components)
1167
1168        profile_plugsets: typing.Optional[
1169            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[items.PlugItemState]]
1170        ] = None
1171
1172        if raw_profile_plugs := payload.get("profilePlugSets"):
1173            profile_plugsets = {
1174                int(index): [self.deserialize_plug_item_state(state) for state in data]
1175                for index, data in raw_profile_plugs["data"]["plugs"].items()
1176            }
1177
1178        character_plugsets: typing.Optional[
1179            collections.Mapping[
1180                int, collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[items.PlugItemState]]
1181            ]
1182        ] = None
1183        if raw_char_plugsets := payload.get("characterPlugSets"):
1184            character_plugsets = {
1185                int(char_id): {
1186                    int(index): [
1187                        self.deserialize_plug_item_state(state) for state in data
1188                    ]
1189                    for index, data in inner["plugs"].items()
1190                }
1191                for char_id, inner in raw_char_plugsets["data"].items()
1192            }
1193
1194        character_collectibles: typing.Optional[
1195            collections.Mapping[int, items.Collectible]
1196        ] = None
1197        if raw_character_collectibles := payload.get("characterCollectibles"):
1198            character_collectibles = {
1199                int(char_id): self._deserialize_collectible(data)
1200                for char_id, data in raw_character_collectibles["data"].items()
1201            }
1202
1203        profile_collectibles: typing.Optional[items.Collectible] = None
1204        if raw_profile_collectibles := payload.get("profileCollectibles"):
1205            profile_collectibles = self._deserialize_collectible(
1206                raw_profile_collectibles["data"]
1207            )
1208
1209        profile_nodes: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, records.Node]] = None
1210        if raw_profile_nodes := payload.get("profilePresentationNodes"):
1211            profile_nodes = {
1212                int(node_hash): self._deserialize_node(node)
1213                for node_hash, node in raw_profile_nodes["data"]["nodes"].items()
1214            }
1215
1216        character_nodes: typing.Optional[
1217            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Mapping[int, records.Node]]
1218        ] = None
1219        if raw_character_nodes := payload.get("characterPresentationNodes"):
1220            character_nodes = {
1221                int(char_id): {
1222                    int(node_hash): self._deserialize_node(node)
1223                    for node_hash, node in each_character["nodes"].items()
1224                }
1225                for char_id, each_character in raw_character_nodes["data"].items()
1226            }
1227
1228        platform_silver: typing.Optional[
1229            collections.Mapping[str, profile.ProfileItemImpl]
1230        ] = None
1231        if raw_platform_silver := payload.get("platformSilver"):
1232            if "data" in raw_platform_silver:
1233                platform_silver = {
1234                    platform_name: self.deserialize_profile_item(item)
1235                    for platform_name, item in raw_platform_silver["data"][
1236                        "platformSilver"
1237                    ].items()
1238                }
1239
1240        character_currency_lookups: typing.Optional[
1241            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[items.Currency]]
1242        ] = None
1243        if raw_char_lookups := payload.get("characterCurrencyLookups"):
1244            if "data" in raw_char_lookups:
1245                character_currency_lookups = {
1246                    int(char_id): self._deserialize_currencies(currencie)
1247                    for char_id, currencie in raw_char_lookups["data"].items()
1248                }
1249
1250        character_craftables: typing.Optional[
1251            collections.Mapping[int, components.CraftablesComponent]
1252        ] = None
1253        if raw_character_craftables := payload.get("characterCraftables"):
1254
1255            if "data" in raw_character_craftables:
1256                character_craftables = {
1257                    int(char_id): self.deserialize_craftables_component(craftable)
1258                    for char_id, craftable in raw_character_craftables["data"].items()
1259                }
1260
1261        return components.Component(
1262            profiles=profile_,
1263            profile_progression=profile_progression,
1264            profile_currencies=profile_currencies,
1265            profile_inventories=profile_inventories,
1266            profile_records=profile_records,
1267            characters=characters,
1268            character_records=character_records,
1269            character_equipments=character_equipments,
1270            character_inventories=character_inventories,
1271            character_activities=character_activities,
1272            character_render_data=character_render_data,
1273            character_progressions=character_progressions,
1274            profile_string_variables=profile_string_vars,
1275            character_string_variables=character_string_vars,
1276            metrics=metrics,
1277            root_node_hash=root_node_hash,
1278            transitory=transitory,
1279            item_components=item_components,
1280            profile_plugsets=profile_plugsets,
1281            character_plugsets=character_plugsets,
1282            character_collectibles=character_collectibles,
1283            profile_collectibles=profile_collectibles,
1284            profile_nodes=profile_nodes,
1285            character_nodes=character_nodes,
1286            platform_silver=platform_silver,
1287            character_currency_lookups=character_currency_lookups,
1288            character_craftables=character_craftables,
1289        )
1290
1291    def deserialize_items_component(
1292        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
1293    ) -> components.ItemsComponent:
1294        instances: typing.Optional[
1295            collections.Sequence[collections.Mapping[int, items.ItemInstance]]
1296        ] = None
1297        if raw_instances := payload.get("instances"):
1298            instances = [
1299                {
1300                    int(ins_id): self.deserialize_instanced_item(item)
1301                    for ins_id, item in raw_instances["data"].items()
1302                }
1303            ]
1304
1305        render_data: typing.Optional[
1306            collections.Mapping[int, tuple[bool, dict[int, int]]]
1307        ] = None
1308        if raw_render_data := payload.get("renderData"):
1309            render_data = {
1310                int(ins_id): (data["useCustomDyes"], data["artRegions"])
1311                for ins_id, data in raw_render_data["data"].items()
1312            }
1313
1314        stats: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, items.ItemStatsView]] = None
1315        if raw_stats := payload.get("stats"):
1316            builder: collections.Mapping[int, items.ItemStatsView] = {}
1317            for ins_id, stat in raw_stats["data"].items():
1318                for _, items_ in stat.items():
1319                    builder[int(ins_id)] = self.deserialize_item_stats_view(items_)  # type: ignore[index]
1320            stats = builder
1321
1322        sockets: typing.Optional[
1323            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[items.ItemSocket]]
1324        ] = None
1325        if raw_sockets := payload.get("sockets"):
1326            sockets = {
1327                int(ins_id): [
1328                    self.deserialize_item_socket(socket) for socket in item["sockets"]
1329                ]
1330                for ins_id, item in raw_sockets["data"].items()
1331            }
1332
1333        objeectives: typing.Optional[
1334            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[records.Objective]]
1335        ] = None
1336        if raw_objectives := payload.get("objectives"):
1337            objeectives = {
1338                int(ins_id): [self.deserialize_objectives(objective)]
1339                for ins_id, data in raw_objectives["data"].items()
1340                for objective in data["objectives"]
1341            }
1342
1343        perks: typing.Optional[
1344            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Collection[items.ItemPerk]]
1345        ] = None
1346        if raw_perks := payload.get("perks"):
1347            perks = {
1348                int(ins_id): [
1349                    self.deserialize_item_perk(perk) for perk in item["perks"]
1350                ]
1351                for ins_id, item in raw_perks["data"].items()
1352            }
1353
1354        plug_states: typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[items.PlugItemState]] = None
1355        if raw_plug_states := payload.get("plugStates"):
1356            pending_states: list[items.PlugItemState] = []
1357            for _, plug in raw_plug_states["data"].items():
1358                pending_states.append(self.deserialize_plug_item_state(plug))
1359            plug_states = pending_states
1360
1361        reusable_plugs: typing.Optional[
1362            collections.Mapping[int, collections.Sequence[items.PlugItemState]]
1363        ] = None
1364        if raw_re_plugs := payload.get("reusablePlugs"):
1365            reusable_plugs = {
1366                int(ins_id): [
1367                    self.deserialize_plug_item_state(state) for state in inner
1368                ]
1369                for ins_id, plug in raw_re_plugs["data"].items()
1370                for inner in list(plug["plugs"].values())
1371            }
1372
1373        plug_objectives: typing.Optional[
1374            collections.Mapping[
1375                int, collections.Mapping[int, collections.Collection[records.Objective]]
1376            ]
1377        ] = None
1378        if raw_plug_objectives := payload.get("plugObjectives"):
1379            plug_objectives = {
1380                int(ins_id): {
1381                    int(obj_hash): [self.deserialize_objectives(obj) for obj in objs]
1382                    for obj_hash, objs in inner["objectivesPerPlug"].items()
1383                }
1384                for ins_id, inner in raw_plug_objectives["data"].items()
1385            }
1386
1387        return components.ItemsComponent(
1388            sockets=sockets,
1389            stats=stats,
1390            render_data=render_data,
1391            instances=instances,
1392            objectives=objeectives,
1393            perks=perks,
1394            plug_states=plug_states,
1395            reusable_plugs=reusable_plugs,
1396            plug_objectives=plug_objectives,
1397        )
1398
1399    def deserialize_character_component(  # type: ignore[call-arg]
1400        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
1401    ) -> components.CharacterComponent:
1402
1403        character_: typing.Optional[character.Character] = None
1404        if raw_singuler_character := payload.get("character"):
1405            character_ = self.deserialize_character(raw_singuler_character["data"])
1406
1407        inventory: typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]] = None
1408        if raw_inventory := payload.get("inventory"):
1409            if "data" in raw_inventory:
1410                inventory = self.deserialize_profile_items(raw_inventory["data"])
1411
1412        activities: typing.Optional[activity.CharacterActivity] = None
1413        if raw_activities := payload.get("activities"):
1414            activities = self.deserialize_character_activity(raw_activities["data"])
1415
1416        equipment: typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[profile.ProfileItemImpl]] = None
1417        if raw_equipments := payload.get("equipment"):
1418            equipment = self.deserialize_profile_items(raw_equipments["data"])
1419
1420        progressions_: typing.Optional[character.CharacterProgression] = None
1421        if raw_progressions := payload.get("progressions"):
1422            progressions_ = self.deserialize_character_progressions(
1423                raw_progressions["data"]
1424            )
1425
1426        render_data: typing.Optional[character.RenderedData] = None
1427        if raw_render_data := payload.get("renderData"):
1428            render_data = self.deserialize_character_render_data(
1429                raw_render_data["data"]
1430            )
1431
1432        character_records: typing.Optional[
1433            collections.Mapping[int, records.CharacterRecord]
1434        ] = None
1435        if raw_char_records := payload.get("records"):
1436            character_records = self.deserialize_characters_records(
1437                raw_char_records["data"]
1438            )
1439
1440        item_components: typing.Optional[components.ItemsComponent] = None
1441        if raw_item_components := payload.get("itemComponents"):
1442            item_components = self.deserialize_items_component(raw_item_components)
1443
1444        nodes: typing.Optional[collections.Mapping[int, records.Node]] = None
1445        if raw_nodes := payload.get("presentationNodes"):
1446            nodes = {
1447                int(node_hash): self._deserialize_node(node)
1448                for node_hash, node in raw_nodes["data"]["nodes"].items()
1449            }
1450
1451        collectibles: typing.Optional[items.Collectible] = None
1452        if raw_collectibles := payload.get("collectibles"):
1453            collectibles = self._deserialize_collectible(raw_collectibles["data"])
1454
1455        currency_lookups: typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[items.Currency]] = None
1456        if raw_currencies := payload.get("currencyLookups"):
1457            if "data" in raw_currencies:
1458                currency_lookups = self._deserialize_currencies(raw_currencies)
1459
1460        return components.CharacterComponent(
1461            activities=activities,
1462            equipment=equipment,
1463            inventory=inventory,
1464            progressions=progressions_,
1465            render_data=render_data,
1466            character=character_,
1467            character_records=character_records,
1468            profile_records=None,
1469            item_components=item_components,
1470            currency_lookups=currency_lookups,
1471            collectibles=collectibles,
1472            nodes=nodes,
1473        )

1475    def _set_entity_attrs(
1476        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject, *, key: str = "displayProperties"
1477    ) -> entity.Entity:
1478
1479        name: undefined.UndefinedOr[str] = undefined.Undefined
1480        description: undefined.UndefinedOr[str] = undefined.Undefined
1481
1482        if properties := payload[key]:
1483            if (raw_name := properties["name"]) is not typedefs.Unknown:
1484                name = raw_name
1485
1486            if (
1487                raw_description := properties["description"]
1488            ) and not typedefs.is_unknown(raw_description):
1489                description = raw_description
1490
1491        return entity.Entity(
1492            net=self._net,
1493            hash=payload["hash"],
1494            index=payload["index"],
1495            name=name,
1496            description=description,
1497            has_icon=properties["hasIcon"],
1498            icon=assets.Image(properties["icon"] if "icon" in properties else None),
1499        )
