1501    def deserialize_inventory_results(
1502        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
1503    ) -> iterators.FlatIterator[entity.SearchableEntity]:
1504        suggested_words: list[str] = payload["suggestedWords"]
1505
1506        def _check_unknown(s: str) -> undefined.UndefinedOr[str]:
1507            return s if not typedefs.is_unknown(s) else undefined.Undefined
1508
1509        return iterators.FlatIterator(
1510            [
1511                entity.SearchableEntity(
1512                    net=self._net,
1513                    hash=data["hash"],
1514                    entity_type=data["entityType"],
1515                    weight=data["weight"],
1516                    suggested_words=suggested_words,
1517                    name=data["displayProperties"]["name"],
1518                    has_icon=data["displayProperties"]["hasIcon"],
1519                    description=_check_unknown(
1520                        data["displayProperties"]["description"]
1521                    ),
1522                    icon=assets.Image(data["displayProperties"]["icon"]),
1523                )
1524                for data in payload["results"]["results"]
1525            ]
1526        )

1576            secondary_special = assets.Image(raw_second_special)

1580            screenshot = assets.Image(raw_screenshot)

1597        if (

1599        ) and not typedefs.is_unknown(raw_ui_style):
1600            ui_item_style = raw_ui_style
1601
1602        tier_and_name: undefined.UndefinedOr[str] = undefined.Undefined
1603        if (
1604            raw_tier_and_name := payload.get("itemTypeAndTierDisplayName")
1605        ) and not typedefs.is_unknown(raw_tier_and_name):
1606            tier_and_name = raw_tier_and_name
1607
1608        type_name: undefined.UndefinedOr[str] = undefined.Undefined

1611        ) and not typedefs.is_unknown(raw_type_name):
1612            type_name = raw_type_name
1613
1614        display_source: undefined.UndefinedOr[str] = undefined.Undefined
1615        if (

1617        ) and not typedefs.is_unknown(raw_display_source):
1618            display_source = raw_display_source
1619
1620        lorehash: typing.Optional[int] = None
1621        if raw_lore_hash := payload.get("loreHash"):
1622            lorehash = int(raw_lore_hash)
1623

1625        if raw_summary_hash := payload.get("summaryItemHash"):
1626            summary_hash = raw_summary_hash
1627

1630            breaker_type_hash = int(raw_breaker_type_hash)
1631

1633        if raw_damage_types := payload.get("damageTypes"):
1634            damage_types = [int(type_) for type_ in raw_damage_types]
1635

1637        if raw_damagetype_hashes := payload.get("damageTypeHashes"):

1639

1648        tier_type: typing.Optional[enums.TierType] = None
1649        tier: typing.Optional[enums.ItemTier] = None

1651        recovery_hash: typing.Optional[int] = None
1652        tier_name: undefined.UndefinedOr[str] = undefined.Undefined
1653        isinstance_item: bool = False
1654        expire_tool_tip: undefined.UndefinedOr[str] = undefined.Undefined
1655        expire_in_orbit_message: undefined.UndefinedOr[str] = undefined.Undefined
1656        suppress_expiration: bool = False
1657        max_stack_size: typing.Optional[int] = None
1658        stack_label: undefined.UndefinedOr[str] = undefined.Undefined
1659
1660        if inventory := payload.get("inventory"):
1661            tier_type = enums.TierType(int(inventory["tierType"]))
1662            tier = enums.ItemTier(int(inventory["tierTypeHash"]))
1663            bucket_hash = int(inventory["bucketTypeHash"])
1664            recovery_hash = int(inventory["recoveryBucketTypeHash"])
1665            tier_name = inventory["tierTypeName"]
1666            isinstance_item = inventory["isInstanceItem"]
1667            suppress_expiration = inventory["suppressExpirationWhenObjectivesComplete"]
1668            max_stack_size = int(inventory["maxStackSize"])
1669
1670            try:
1671                stack_label = inventory["stackUniqueLabel"]
1672            except KeyError:
1673                pass
1674
1675        return entity.InventoryEntity(
1676            net=self._net,
1677            collectible_hash=collectible_hash,
1678            name=props.name,
1679            about=about,
1680            emblem_objective_hash=emblem_objective_hash,
1681            suppress_expiration=suppress_expiration,
1682            max_stack_size=max_stack_size,
1683            stack_label=stack_label,
1684            tier=tier,
1685            tier_type=tier_type,
1686            tier_name=tier_name,
1687            bucket_hash=bucket_hash,
1688            recovery_bucket_hash=recovery_hash,
1689            isinstance_item=isinstance_item,
1690            expire_in_orbit_message=expire_in_orbit_message,
1691            expiration_tooltip=expire_tool_tip,
1692            lore_hash=lorehash,
1693            type_and_tier_name=tier_and_name,
1694            summary_hash=summary_hash,
1695            ui_display_style=ui_item_style,
1696            type_name=type_name,
1697            breaker_type_hash=breaker_type_hash,
1698            description=props.description,
1699            display_source=display_source,
1700            hash=props.hash,
1701            damage_types=damage_types,
1702            index=props.index,
1703            icon=props.icon,
1704            has_icon=props.has_icon,
1705            screenshot=screenshot,
1706            watermark_icon=watermark_icon,
1707            watermark_shelved=watermark_shelved,
1708            secondary_icon=secondary_icon,
1709            secondary_overlay=secondary_overlay,
1710            secondary_special=secondary_special,
1711            type=enums.ItemType(int(payload["itemType"])),
1712            trait_hashes=[int(id_) for id_ in payload.get("traitHashes", [])],
1713            trait_ids=[trait for trait in payload.get("traitIds", [])],
1714            category_hashes=[int(hash_) for hash_ in payload["itemCategoryHashes"]],
1715            item_class=enums.Class(int(payload["classType"])),
1716            sub_type=enums.ItemSubType(int(payload["itemSubType"])),
1717            breaker_type=int(payload["breakerType"]),
1718            default_damagetype=int(payload["defaultDamageType"]),
1719            default_damagetype_hash=default_damagetype_hash,
1720            damagetype_hashes=damagetype_hashes,
1721            tooltip_notifications=payload["tooltipNotifications"],

1726            background_colors=payload.get("backgroundColor", {}),
1727            season_hash=payload.get("seasonHash"),
1728            has_postmaster_effect=payload["doesPostmasterPullHaveSideEffects"],
1729        )

1794    def deserialize_activity(
1795        self,
1796        payload: typedefs.JSONObject,
1797        /,
1798    ) -> activity.Activity:
1799        period = time.clean_date(payload["period"])
1800        details = payload["activityDetails"]
1801        ref_id = int(details["referenceId"])
1802        instance_id = int(details["instanceId"])
1803        mode = enums.GameMode(details["mode"])
1804        modes = [enums.GameMode(int(mode_)) for mode_ in details["modes"]]
1805        is_private = details["isPrivate"]
1806        membership_type = enums.MembershipType(int(details["membershipType"]))
1807
1808        # Since we're using the same fields for post activity method
1809        # this check is required since post activity doesn't values values
1810        values = self._deserialize_activity_values(payload["values"])
1811
1812        return activity.Activity(
1813            net=self._net,
1814            hash=ref_id,
1815            instance_id=instance_id,
1816            mode=mode,
1817            modes=modes,
1818            is_private=is_private,
1819            membership_type=membership_type,
1820            occurred_at=period,
1821            values=values,
1822        )

1830                for activity_ in payload["activities"]

1998    def deserialize_linked_profiles(
1999        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
2000    ) -> profile.LinkedProfile:
2001        bungie_user = self.deserialize_partial_bungie_user(payload["bnetMembership"])
2002        error_profiles_vec: typing.MutableSequence[user.DestinyMembership] = []
2003        profiles_vec: typing.MutableSequence[user.DestinyMembership] = []
2004
2005        if raw_profile := payload.get("profiles"):
2006            for pfile in raw_profile:
2007                profiles_vec.append(self.deserialize_destiny_membership(pfile))
2008
2009        if raw_profiles_with_errors := payload.get("profilesWithErrors"):
2010            for raw_error_pfile in raw_profiles_with_errors:
2011                if error_pfile := raw_error_pfile.get("infoCard"):
2012                    error_profiles_vec.append(
2013                        self.deserialize_destiny_membership(error_pfile)
2014                    )
2015
2016        return profile.LinkedProfile(
2017            net=self._net,
2018            bungie=bungie_user,
2019            profiles=profiles_vec,
2020            profiles_with_errors=error_profiles_vec,
2021        )

2024        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
2025    ) -> collections.Sequence[clans.ClanBanner]:
2026        banners_seq: typing.MutableSequence[clans.ClanBanner] = []
2027        if banners := payload.get("clanBannerDecals"):

2030                    id=int(k),
2031                    foreground=assets.Image(v["foregroundPath"]),
2032                    background=assets.Image(v["backgroundPath"]),

2035        return banners_seq

2037    def deserialize_public_milestone_content(
2038        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
2039    ) -> milestones.MilestoneContent:
2040        items_categoris: typedefs.NoneOr[milestones.MilestoneItems] = None
2041        if raw_categories := payload.get("itemCategories"):
2042            for item in raw_categories:
2043                title = undefined.Undefined
2044                if raw_title := item.get("title"):
2045                    if raw_title != typedefs.Unknown:
2046                        title = raw_title
2047                if raw_hashes := item.get("itemHashes"):
2048                    hashes: collections.Sequence[int] = raw_hashes
2049
2050                items_categoris = milestones.MilestoneItems(title=title, hashes=hashes)
2051
2052        about = undefined.Undefined
2053        if (raw_about := payload["about"]) != typedefs.Unknown:
2054            about = raw_about
2055
2056        status = undefined.Undefined
2057        if (raw_status := payload["status"]) != typedefs.Unknown:
2058            status = raw_status
2059
2060        tips: typing.MutableSequence[undefined.UndefinedOr[str]] = []
2061        if raw_tips := payload.get("tips"):
2062            for raw_tip in raw_tips:
2063                if raw_tip == typedefs.Unknown:
2064                    raw_tip = undefined.Undefined
2065                tips.append(raw_tip)
2066
2067        return milestones.MilestoneContent(
2068            about=about, status=status, tips=tips, items=items_categoris
2069        )

2103        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
2104    ) -> friends.FriendRequestView:

2107

2141    def deserialize_fireteams(
2142        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
2143    ) -> typedefs.NoneOr[collections.Sequence[fireteams.Fireteam]]:
2144        fireteams_: typing.MutableSequence[fireteams.Fireteam] = []
2145
2146        result: list[typedefs.JSONObject]
2147        if not (result := payload["results"]):
2148            return None
2149        for elem in result:
2150            fireteams_.append(
2151                self._set_fireteam_fields(

2153                )
2154            )
2155        return fireteams_

2180    def deserialize_fireteam_members(
2181        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject, *, alternatives: bool = False
2182    ) -> typing.Optional[collections.Sequence[fireteams.FireteamMember]]:
2183        members_: list[fireteams.FireteamMember] = []
2184        if members := payload.get("Members" if not alternatives else "Alternates"):
2185            for member in members:
2186                bungie_fields = self.deserialize_partial_bungie_user(member)
2187                members_fields = fireteams.FireteamMember(
2188                    destiny_user=self.deserialize_fireteam_destiny_users(member),
2189                    has_microphone=member["hasMicrophone"],
2190                    character_id=int(member["characterId"]),
2191                    date_joined=time.clean_date(member["dateJoined"]),
2192                    last_platform_invite_date=time.clean_date(
2193                        member["lastPlatformInviteAttemptDate"]
2194                    ),
2195                    last_platform_invite_result=int(

The base deserialization factory class for all aiobungie objects.

Highly inspired hikari entity factory used to deserialize JSON responses from the REST client and turning them into a aiobungie.crate Python classes.

#   def deserialize_clan_conversations( self, payload: list[typing.Any] ) -> collections.abc.Sequence[aiobungie.crate.clans.ClanConversation]:
View Source 
345    def deserialize_clan_conversations(
346        self, payload: typedefs.JSONArray
347    ) -> collections.Sequence[clans.ClanConversation]:
348        map = {}
349        vec: list[clans.ClanConversation] = []
350        if payload:
351            for convo in payload:
352                for k, v in convo.items():
353                    map[k] = v
354
355                name: undefined.UndefinedOr[str] = undefined.Undefined
356                if (raw_name := map["chatName"]) and not typedefs.is_unknown(raw_name):
357                    name = raw_name
358
359                convo_obj = clans.ClanConversation(
360                    net=self._net,
361                    group_id=int(map["groupId"]),
362                    id=int(map["conversationId"]),
363                    chat_enabled=map["chatEnabled"],
364                    name=name,
365                    security=map["chatSecurity"],
366                )
367                vec.append(convo_obj)
368        return vec

#   def deserialize_profile( self, payload: dict[str, typing.Any], / ) -> Optional[aiobungie.crate.profile.Profile]:
View Source 
417    def deserialize_profile(
418        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject, /
419    ) -> typing.Optional[profile.Profile]:
420        if (raw_profile := payload.get("data")) is None:
421            return None
422
423        payload = raw_profile
424        id = int(payload["userInfo"]["membershipId"])
425        name = payload["userInfo"]["displayName"]
426        is_public = payload["userInfo"]["isPublic"]
427        type = enums.MembershipType(payload["userInfo"]["membershipType"])
428        last_played = time.clean_date(str(payload["dateLastPlayed"]))
429        character_ids = [int(cid) for cid in payload["characterIds"]]
430        power_cap = payload["currentSeasonRewardPowerCap"]
431
432        return profile.Profile(
433            id=int(id),
434            name=name,
435            is_public=is_public,
436            type=type,
437            last_played=last_played,
438            character_ids=character_ids,

2102    def deserialize_friend_requests(
2103        self, payload: typedefs.JSONObject
2104    ) -> friends.FriendRequestView:

2106        outgoing: typing.MutableSequence[friends.Friend] = []

2113            for outgoing_request in raw_outgoing_requests:

101class Flag(__enum.Flag):
102    """Builtin Python enum flag with extra handlings."""
103
104    # Needs to type this here for mypy
105    _value_: int
106
107    @property
108    def name(self) -> str:  # type: ignore[override]
109        if self._name_ is None:
110            self._name_ = f"UNKNOWN {self._value_}"
111
112        return self._name_
113
114    @property
115    def value(self) -> int:  # type: ignore[override]
116        return self._value_
117
118    def __str__(self) -> str:
119        return self.name
120
121    def __repr__(self) -> str:
122        return f"<{type(self).__name__}.{self.name}: {self._value_!s}>"
123
124    def __int__(self) -> int:
125        if isinstance(self.value, _ITERABLE):
126            raise TypeError(
127                f"Can't overload {self.value} in {type(self).__name__}, Please use `.value` attribute.",
128            )
129        return int(self.value)
130
131    def __or__(self, other: typing.Union[Flag, int]) -> Flag:
132        return self.__class__(self._value_ | int(other))
133
134    def __xor__(self, other: typing.Union[Flag, int]) -> Flag:
135        return self.__class__(self._value_ ^ int(other))
136
137    def __and__(self, other: typing.Union[Flag, int]) -> Flag:
138        return self.__class__(other & int(other))
139
140    def __invert__(self) -> Flag:
141        return self.__class__(~self._value_)
142
143    def __contains__(self, other: typing.Union[Flag, int]) -> bool:
144        return self.value & int(other) == int(other)

#   class FlatIterator(typing.Generic[~Item]):

 42class FlatIterator(typing.Generic[Item]):
 43    """A Flat, In-Memory iterator for sequenced based data.
 44
 45    This can either be used sync or asynchronously.
 46
 47    Example
 48    -------
 49    ```py
 50    iterator = FlatIterator([1, 2, 3])
 51
 52    # Limit the results to 2.
 53    async for item in iterator.take(2):
 54        print(item)
 55    # 1
 56    # 2
 57
 58    # Filter the results.
 59    async for item in iterator.filter(lambda item: item > 1):
 60        print(item)
 61        print(iterator.count())
 62    # 2
 63    # 3
 64    # 3
 65
 66    # Map the results.
 67    async for item in iterator.map(lambda item: item * 2):
 68        print(item)
 69    # 2
 70    # 4
 71
 72    # This also works synchronously.
 73    iterator = FlatIterator(["Hello", "World", "!"])
 74    for item in iterator.discard(lambda item: "!" in item):
 75        print(item)
 76    # Hello
 77    # World
 78
 79    # Indexing is also supported.
 80
 81    print(iterator[0])
 82    # Hello
 83    ```
 84
 85    Parameters
 86    ----------
 87    items: `collections.Iterable[Item]`
 88        The items to iterate over.
 89    """
 90
 91    __slots__ = ("_items",)
 92
 93    def __init__(self, items: collections.Iterable[Item]) -> None:
 94        self._items = iter(items)
 95
 96    @typing.overload
 97    def collect(self) -> list[Item]:
 98        ...
 99
100    @typing.overload
101    def collect(self, casting: _B) -> list[_B]:
102        """Collects all items in the iterator into a list and cast them into an object if provided.
103
104        Example
105        -------
106        >>> iterator = FlatIterator([1, 2, 3])
107        >>> iterator.collect(casting=str)
108        ["1", "2", "3"]
109
110        Parameters
111        ----------
112        casting: `T | None`
113            The type to cast the items to. If `None` is provided, the items will be returned as is.
114
115        Raises
116        ------
117        `StopIteration`
118            If no elements are left in the iterator.
119        """
120        ...
121
122    def collect(
123        self, casting: typing.Optional[_B] = None
124    ) -> typing.Union[list[Item], list[_B]]:
125        """Collects all items in the iterator into a list.
126
127        Example
128        -------
129        >>> iterator = FlatIterator([1, 2, 3])
130        >>> iterator.collect()
131        [1, 2, 3]
132
133        Raises
134        ------
135        `StopIteration`
136            If no elements are left in the iterator.
137        """
138        if casting is not None:
139            return typing.cast(list[_B], list(map(casting, self._items)))
140
141        return list(self._items)
142
143    def next(self) -> Item:
144        """Returns the next item in the iterator.
145
146        Example
147        -------
148        >>> iterator = FlatIterator[str](["1", "2", "3"])
149        item = iterator.next()
150        assert item == "1"
151        item = iterator.next()
152        assert item == "2"
153
154        Raises
155        ------
156        `StopIteration`
157            If no elements are left in the iterator.
158        """
159        try:
160            return self.__next__()
161        except StopIteration:
162            self._ok()
163
164    def map(
165        self, predicate: collections.Callable[[Item], OtherItem]
166    ) -> FlatIterator[OtherItem]:
167        """Maps each item in the iterator to its predicated value.
168
169        Example
170        -------
171        >>> iterator = FlatIterator[str](["1", "2", "3"]).map(lambda value: int(value))
172        <FlatIterator([1, 2, 3])>
173        >>> async for item in iterator:
174                assert isinstance(item, int)
175
176        Parameters
177        ----------
178        predicate: `collections.Callable[[Item], Item]`
179            The function to map each item in the iterator to its predicated value.
180
181        Raises
182        ------
183        `StopIteration`
184            If no elements are left in the iterator.
185        """
186        return FlatIterator(map(predicate, self._items))
187
188    def take(self, n: int) -> FlatIterator[Item]:
189        """Take the first number of items until the number of items are yielded or
190        the end of the iterator is reached.
191
192        Example
193        -------
194        >>> iterator = FlatIterator([GameMode.RAID, GameMode.STRIKE, GameMode.GAMBIT])
195        >>> async for mode in iterator.take(2):
196                assert mode in [GameMode.RAID, GameMode.STRIKE]
197        <FlatIterator([GameMode.RAID, GameMode.STRIKE])>
198
199        Parameters
200        ----------
201        n: `int`
202            The number of items to take.
203
204        Raises
205        ------
206        `StopIteration`
207            If no elements are left in the iterator.
208        """
209        return FlatIterator(itertools.islice(self._items, n))
210
211    def take_while(
212        self, predicate: collections.Callable[[Item], bool]
213    ) -> FlatIterator[Item]:
214        """Yields items from the iterator while predicate returns `True`.
215
216        Example
217        -------
218        ```py
219        iterator = FlatIterator([MembershipType.STEAM, MembershipType.XBOX, MembershipType.STADIA])
220
221        async for platform in (
222            iterator
223            .take_while(lambda platform: platform is not MembershipType.XBOX)
224        ):
225                print(platform)
226        # <FlatIterator([MembershipType.STEAM])>
227        ```
228
229        Parameters
230        ----------
231        predicate: `collections.Callable[[Item], bool]`
232            The function to predicate each item in the iterator.
233
234        Raises
235        ------
236        `StopIteration`
237            If no elements are left in the iterator.
238        """
239        return FlatIterator(itertools.takewhile(predicate, self._items))
240
241    def drop_while(
242        self, predicate: collections.Callable[[Item], bool]
243    ) -> FlatIterator[Item]:
244        """Yields items from the iterator while predicate returns `False`.
245
246        Example
247        -------
248        ```py
249        iterator = FlatIterator(
250            [DestinyMembership(name="Fate"), DestinyMembership(name="Jim"), DestinyMembership(name="Bob")]
251        )
252
253        async for membership in (
254            iterator
255            .drop_while(lambda membership: membership.name is not "Jim")
256        ):
257                print(membership)
258        # <FlatIterator([DestinyMembership(name="Bob")])>
259        ```
260
261        Parameters
262        ----------
263        predicate: `collections.Callable[[Item], bool]`
264            The function to predicate each item in the iterator.
265
266        Raises
267        ------
268        `StopIteration`
269            If no elements are left in the iterator.
270        """
271        return FlatIterator(itertools.dropwhile(predicate, self._items))
272
273    def filter(
274        self, predicate: collections.Callable[[Item], bool]
275    ) -> FlatIterator[Item]:
276        """Filters the iterator to only yield items that match the predicate.
277
278        Example
279        -------
280        ```py
281        activities = FlatIterator(
282            [Activity(mode=GameMode.RAID), Activity(mode=GameMode.DUNGEON), Activity(mode=GameMode.STRIKE)]
283            # Assuming Raid is solo, Strike is flawless.
284        )
285
286        async for activity in (
287            activities
288            .filter(lambda activity: activity.is_solo or activity.is_flawless)
289        ):
290                print(member)
291        # <FlatIterator([Activity(mode=GameMode.RAID), Activity(mode=GameMode.STRIKE)])>
292        ```
293        """
294        return FlatIterator(filter(predicate, self._items))
295
296    def skip(self, n: int) -> FlatIterator[Item]:
297        """Skips the first number of items in the iterator.
298
299        Example
300        -------
301        ```py
302        iterator = FlatIterator([MembershipType.STEAM, MembershipType.XBOX, MembershipType.STADIA])
303
304        async for platform in iterator.skip(1):
305                print(platform)
306        # Skip the first item in the iterator.
307        # <FlatIterator([MembershipType.XBOX, MembershipType.STADIA])>
308        """
309        return FlatIterator(itertools.islice(self._items, n, None))
310
311    def discard(
312        self, predicate: collections.Callable[[Item], bool]
313    ) -> FlatIterator[Item]:
314        """Discards all elements in the iterator for which the predicate function returns true.
315
316        Example
317        -------
318        >>> iterator = FlatIterator([MembershipType.STEAM, MembershipType.XBOX, MembershipType.STADIA])
319        >>> async for _ in iterator.discard(lambda platform: platform is not MembershipType.STEAM):
320                # Drops all memberships that are not steam.
321                print(iterator)
322        <FlatIterator([MembershipType.XBOX, MembershipType.STADIA])>
323
324        Parameters
325        ----------
326        predicate: `collections.Callable[[Item], bool]`
327            The function to test each item in the iterator.
328
329        Raises
330        ------
331        `StopIteration`
332            If no elements are left in the iterator.
333        """
334        return FlatIterator(filter(lambda x: not predicate(x), self._items))
335
336    def zip(
337        self, other: FlatIterator[OtherItem]
338    ) -> FlatIterator[tuple[Item, OtherItem]]:
339        """Zips the iterator with another iterable.
340
341        Example
342        -------
343        >>> iterator = FlatIterator([1, 2, 3])
344        >>> other = FlatIterator([4, 5, 6])
345        >>> async for item, other_item in iterator.zip(other):
346                assert item == other_item
347        <FlatIterator([(1, 4), (2, 5), (3, 6)])>
348
349        Parameters
350        ----------
351        other: `FlatIterator[OtherItem]`
352            The iterable to zip with.
353
354        Raises
355        ------
356        `StopIteration`
357            If no elements are left in the iterator.
358        """
359        return FlatIterator(zip(self._items, other))
360
361    def all(self, predicate: collections.Callable[[Item], bool]) -> bool:
362        """`True` if all items in the iterator match the predicate.
363
364        Example
365        -------
366        >>> iterator = FlatIterator([1, 2, 3])
367        >>> while iterator.all(lambda item: isinstance(item, int)):
368                print("Still all integers")
369                continue
370            # Still all integers
371
372        Parameters
373        ----------
374        predicate: `collections.Callable[[Item], bool]`
375            The function to test each item in the iterator.
376
377        Raises
378        ------
379        `StopIteration`
380            If no elements are left in the iterator.
381        """
382        return all(predicate(item) for item in self)
383
384    def any(self, predicate: collections.Callable[[Item], bool]) -> bool:
385        """`True` if any items in the iterator match the predicate.
386
387        Example
388        -------
389        >>> iterator = FlatIterator([1, 2, 3])
390        >>> if iterator.any(lambda item: isinstance(item, int)):
391                print("At least one item is an int.")
392        # At least one item is an int.
393
394        Parameters
395        ----------
396        predicate: `collections.Callable[[Item], bool]`
397            The function to test each item in the iterator.
398
399        Raises
400        ------
401        `StopIteration`
402            If no elements are left in the iterator.
403        """
404        return any(predicate(item) for item in self)
405
406    def sort(
407        self,
408        *,
409        key: collections.Callable[[Item], typeshed.SupportsRichComparison],
410        reverse: bool = False,
411    ) -> FlatIterator[Item]:
412        """Sorts the iterator.
413
414        Example
415        -------
416        >>> iterator = FlatIterator([3, 1, 6, 7])
417        >>> async for item in iterator.sort(key=lambda item: item < 3):
418                print(item)
419        # 1
420        # 3
421        # 6
422        # 7
423
424        Parameters
425        ----------
426        key: `collections.Callable[[Item], Any]`
427            The function to sort by.
428        reverse: `bool`
429            Whether to reverse the sort.
430
431        Raises
432        ------
433        `StopIteration`
434            If no elements are left in the iterator.
435        """
436        return FlatIterator(sorted(self._items, key=key, reverse=reverse))
437
438    def first(self) -> Item:
439        """Returns the first item in the iterator.
440
441        Example
442        -------
443        >>> iterator = FlatIterator([3, 1, 6, 7])
444        >>> iterator.first()
445        3
446
447        Raises
448        ------
449        `StopIteration`
450            If no elements are left in the iterator.
451        """
452        return self.take(1).next()
453
454    def reversed(self) -> FlatIterator[Item]:
455        """Returns a new iterator that yields the items in the iterator in reverse order.
456
457        Example
458        -------
459        >>> iterator = FlatIterator([3, 1, 6, 7])
460        >>> async for item in iterator.reversed():
461                print(item)
462        # 7
463        # 6
464        # 1
465        # 3
466
467        Raises
468        ------
469        `StopIteration`
470            If no elements are left in the iterator.
471        """
472        return FlatIterator(reversed(self.collect()))
473
474    def count(self) -> int:
475        count = 0
476        for _ in self:
477            count += 1
478
479        return count

481    def union(self, other: FlatIterator[Item]) -> FlatIterator[Item]:
482        """Returns a new iterator that yields all items from both iterators.
483
484        Example
485        -------
486        >>> iterator = FlatIterator([1, 2, 3])
487        >>> other = FlatIterator([4, 5, 6])
488        >>> async for item in iterator.union(other):
489                print(item)
490        # 1
491        # 2
492        # 3
493        # 4
494        # 5
495        # 6
496
497        Parameters
498        ----------
499        other: `FlatIterator[Item]`
500            The iterable to union with.
501
502        Raises
503        ------
504        `StopIteration`
505            If no elements are left in the iterator.
506        """
507        return FlatIterator(itertools.chain(self._items, other))
508
509    def for_each(self, func: collections.Callable[[Item], typing.Any]) -> None:
510        """Calls the function on each item in the iterator.
511
512        Example
513        -------
514        >>> iterator = FlatIterator([1, 2, 3])
515        >>> iterator.for_each(lambda item: print(item))
516        # 1
517        # 2
518        # 3
519
520        Parameters
521        ----------
522        func: `typeshed.Callable[[Item], None]`
523            The function to call on each item in the iterator.
524        """
525        for item in self:
526            func(item)
527
528    def enumerate(self, *, start: int = 0) -> FlatIterator[tuple[int, Item]]:
529        """Returns a new iterator that yields tuples of the index and item.
530
531        Example
532        -------
533        >>> iterator = FlatIterator([1, 2, 3])
534        >>> async for index, item in iterator.enumerate():
535                print(index, item)
536
537        # 0, 1
538        # 1, 2
539        # 2, 3
540
541        Raises
542        ------
543        `StopIteration`
544            If no elements are left in the iterator.
545        """
546        return FlatIterator(enumerate(self._items, start=start))
547
548    def _ok(self) -> typing.NoReturn:
549        raise StopIteration("No more items in the iterator.") from None
550
551    def __getitem__(self, index: int) -> Item:
552        try:
553            return self.skip(index).first()
554        except IndexError:
555            self._ok()
556
557    # This is a never.
558    def __setitem__(self) -> typing.NoReturn:
559        raise TypeError(
560            f"{type(self).__name__} doesn't support item assignment."
561        ) from None
562
563    def __repr__(self) -> str:
564        return f'<{self.__class__.__name__}({", ".join([str(item) for item in self])})>'
565
566    def __len__(self) -> int:
567        return self.count()

569    # We support both sync and async iter.
570    def __iter__(self) -> FlatIterator[Item]:
571        return self

573    def __aiter__(self) -> FlatIterator[Item]:
574        return self

576    def __next__(self) -> Item:
577        try:
578            item = next(self._items)
579        except StopIteration:

584    async def __anext__(self) -> Item:
585        try:
586            item = next(self._items)
587        except StopIteration as e:
588            raise StopAsyncIteration from e

A Flat, In-Memory iterator for sequenced based data.

This can either be used sync or asynchronously.

Example
iterator = FlatIterator([1, 2, 3])

# Limit the results to 2.
async for item in iterator.take(2):
    print(item)
# 1
# 2

# Filter the results.
async for item in iterator.filter(lambda item: item > 1):
    print(item)
    print(iterator.count())
# 2
# 3
# 3

# Map the results.
async for item in iterator.map(lambda item: item * 2):
    print(item)
# 2
# 4

# This also works synchronously.
iterator = FlatIterator(["Hello", "World", "!"])
for item in iterator.discard(lambda item: "!" in item):
    print(item)
# Hello
# World

# Indexing is also supported.

print(iterator[0])
# Hello

 85@attrs.define(auto_exc=True, kw_only=True)
 86class HTTPException(HTTPError):
 87    """Exception base internally used for an HTTP request response errors."""
 88
 89    error_code: int
 90    """The returned Bungie error status code."""
 91
 92    http_status: http.HTTPStatus
 93    """The request response http status."""
 94
 95    throttle_seconds: int
 96    """The Bungie response throttle seconds."""
 97
 98    url: typing.Optional[typedefs.StrOrURL]
 99    """The URL/endpoint caused this error."""
100
101    body: typing.Any
102    """The response body."""
103
104    headers: multidict.CIMultiDictProxy[str]
105    """The response headers."""
106
107    message: str
108    """A Bungie human readable message describes the cause of the error."""
109
110    error_status: str
111    """A Bungie short error status describes the cause of the error."""
112
113    message_data: dict[str, str]
114    """A dict of string key, value that includes each cause of the error
115    to a message describes information about that error.
116    """
117
118    def __str__(self) -> str:
119        if self.message:
120            message_body = self.message
121
122        if self.error_status:
123            error_status_body = self.error_status
124
125        return (
126            f"{self.http_status.name.replace('_', '').title()} {self.http_status.value}: "
127            f"Error status: {error_status_body}, Error message: {message_body} from {self.url} "
128            f"{str(self.body)}"
129        )

#   class Image:
View Source 
 71class Image:
 72    """Representation of an image/avatar/picture at Bungie.
 73
 74    Example
 75    -------
 76    ```py
 77    from aiobungie import Image
 78    img = Image("img/destiny_content/pgcr/raid_eclipse.jpg")
 79    print(img)
 80    # https://www.bungie.net/img/destiny_content/pgcr/raid_eclipse.jpg
 81
 82    # Stream the image.
 83    async for chunk in img:
 84        # Byte chunks of the image.
 85        print(chunk)
 86
 87    # Save the image to a file.
 88    await img.save("file_name", "/my/path/to/save/to", "jpeg")
 89    ```
 90
 91    Parameters
 92    ----------
 93    path : `str | None`
 94        The path to the image. If `None`, the default missing image path will be used.
 95    """
 96
 97    __slots__ = ("_path",)
 98
 99    def __init__(self, path: typing.Optional[str] = None) -> None:
100        self._path = path
101
102    @property
103    def is_missing(self) -> bool:
104        return not self._path
105
106    @property
107    def url(self) -> str:
108        """The URL to the image."""
109        return self.create_url()
110
111    @staticmethod
112    def missing_path() -> str:
113        """Returns the path to the missing Bungie image."""
114        return "img/misc/missing_icon_d2.png"
115
116    def create_url(self) -> str:
117        """Creates a full URL to the image path.
118
119        Returns
120        -------
121        str
122            The URL to the image.
123        """
124        return f"{url.BASE}/{self._path if self._path else self.missing_path()}"
125
126    async def save(
127        self,
128        file_name: str,
129        path: typing.Union[pathlib.Path, str],
130        /,
131        mime_type: typing.Optional[typing.Union[MimeType, str]] = None,
132    ) -> None:
133        """Saves the image to a file.
134
135        Parameters
136        ----------
137        file_name : `str`
138            A name for the file to save the image to.
139        path : `pathlib.Path | str`
140            A path tp save the image to.
141
142        Other Parameters
143        ----------------
144        mime_type : `MimeType | str`
145            Optional MIME type of the image.
146
147        Raises
148        ------
149        `FileNotFoundError`
150            If the path provided does not exist.
151        `RuntimeError`
152            If the image could not be saved.
153        `PermissionError`
154            If the path provided is not writable or does not have write permissions.
155        """
156        if isinstance(path, pathlib.Path) and not path.exists():
157            raise FileNotFoundError(f"File does not exist: {path!r}")
158
159        if self.is_missing:
160            return
161
162        mimetype = mime_type or MimeType.PNG
163        path = pathlib.Path(path)
164
165        loop = helpers.get_or_make_loop()
166        pool = concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor()
167
168        try:
169            with pool:
170                await loop.run_in_executor(
171                    pool, _write, path, file_name, mimetype, await self.read()
172                )
173                _LOGGER.info("Saved image to %s", file_name)
174
175        except asyncio.CancelledError:
176            pass
177
178        except Exception as err:
179            raise RuntimeError("Encountered an error while saving image.") from err
180
181    async def read(self) -> bytes:
182        """Read this image bytes.
183
184        Returns
185        -------
186        `bytes`
187            The bytes of this image.
188        """
189        client_session = aiohttp.ClientSession()
190
191        try:
192            await client_session.__aenter__()
193            response = await client_session.get(self.create_url())
194
195            if 300 >= response.status >= 200:
196                reader = await response.read()
197
198        except Exception as exc:
199            raise RuntimeError(f"Failed to read image: {exc}") from None
200        finally:
201            await client_session.__aexit__(None, None, None)
202        return reader
203
204    async def iter(self) -> collections.AsyncGenerator[bytes, None]:
205        """Iterates over the image bytes lazily.
206
207        Example
208        -------
209        import aiobungie
210
211        resource = aiobungie.Image("img/misc/missing_icon_d2.png")
212        async for chunk in resource.iter():
213            print(chunk)
214
215        Returns
216        -------
217        `collections.AsyncGenerator[bytes, None]`
218            An async generator of the image bytes.
219        """
220
221        async for chunk in self:
222            yield chunk
223
224    def __repr__(self) -> str:
225        return f"Image(url={self.create_url()})"
226
227    def __str__(self) -> str:
228        return self.create_url()
229
230    def __aiter__(self) -> Image:
231        return self
232
233    async def __anext__(self) -> bytes:
234        return await self.read()
235
236    def __await__(self) -> collections.Generator[None, None, bytes]:
237        return self.__anext__().__await__()

Representation of an image/avatar/picture at Bungie.

Example
from aiobungie import Image
img = Image("img/destiny_content/pgcr/raid_eclipse.jpg")
print(img)
# https://www.bungie.net/img/destiny_content/pgcr/raid_eclipse.jpg

# Stream the image.
async for chunk in img:
    # Byte chunks of the image.
    print(chunk)

# Save the image to a file.
await img.save("file_name", "/my/path/to/save/to", "jpeg")

175@attrs.define(auto_exc=True)
176class MembershipTypeError(BadRequest):
177    """A bad request error raised when passing wrong membership to the request.
178
179    Those fields are useful since it returns the correct membership and id which can be used
180    to make the request again with those fields.
181    """
182
183    membership_type: str = attrs.field(default="")
184    """The errored membership type passed to the request."""
185
186    membership_id: int = attrs.field(default=0)
187    """The errored user's membership id."""
188
189    required_membership: str = attrs.field(default="")
190    """The required correct membership for errored user."""
191
192    def __str__(self) -> str:
193        return (
194            f"Expected membership: {self.required_membership}, "
195            f"But got {self.membership_type} for id {self.membership_id}"
196        )
197
198    def __int__(self) -> int:
199        return int(self.membership_id)

#   class RESTClient(aiobungie.interfaces.rest.RESTInterface):
View Source 
 366class RESTClient(interfaces.RESTInterface):
 367    """A RESTful client implementation for Bungie's API.
 368
 369    This client is designed to only make HTTP requests and return JSON objects
 370    to provide RESTful functionality.
 371
 372    This client is also used within `aiobungie.Client` which deserialize those returned JSON objects
 373    using the factory into Pythonic data classes objects which provide Python functionality.
 374
 375    Example
 376    -------
 377    ```py
 378    import aiobungie
 379
 380    async def main():
 381        async with aiobungie.RESTClient("TOKEN") as rest_client:
 382            req = await rest_client.fetch_clan_members(4389205)
 383            clan_members = req['results']
 384            for member in clan_members:
 385                for k, v in member['destinyUserInfo'].items():
 386                    print(k, v)
 387    ```
 388
 389    Parameters
 390    ----------
 391    token : `str`
 392        A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
 393
 394    Other Parameters
 395    ----------------
 396    max_retries : `int`
 397        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `5xx` status code.
 398    max_ratelimit_retries : `int`
 399        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `429` status code. Defaults to `3`.
 400    client_secret : `typing.Optional[str]`
 401        An optional application client secret,
 402        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
 403    client_id : `typing.Optional[int]`
 404        An optional application client id,
 405        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
 406    enable_debugging : `bool | str`
 407        Whether to enable logging responses or not.
 408
 409    Logging Levels
 410    --------------
 411    * `False`: This will disable logging.
 412    * `True`: This will set the level to `DEBUG` and enable logging minimal information.
 413    Like the response status, route, taken time and so on.
 414    * `"TRACE" | aiobungie.TRACE`: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.
 415    """
 416
 417    __slots__ = (
 418        "_token",
 419        "_session",
 420        "_lock",
 421        "_max_retries",
 422        "_client_secret",
 423        "_client_id",
 424        "_metadata",
 425        "_max_rate_limit_retries",
 426    )
 427
 428    def __init__(
 429        self,
 430        token: str,
 431        /,
 432        client_secret: typing.Optional[str] = None,
 433        client_id: typing.Optional[int] = None,
 434        *,
 435        max_retries: int = 4,
 436        max_ratelimit_retries: int = 3,
 437        enable_debugging: typing.Union[typing.Literal["TRACE"], bool, int] = False,
 438    ) -> None:
 439        self._session: typing.Optional[_Session] = None
 440        self._lock: typing.Optional[asyncio.Lock] = None
 441        self._client_secret = client_secret
 442        self._client_id = client_id
 443        self._token: str = token
 444        self._max_retries = max_retries
 445        self._max_rate_limit_retries = max_ratelimit_retries
 446        self._metadata: collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any] = {}
 447
 448        self._set_debug_level(enable_debugging)
 449
 450    @property
 451    def client_id(self) -> typing.Optional[int]:
 452        return self._client_id
 453
 454    @property
 455    def metadata(self) -> collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any]:
 456        return self._metadata
 457
 458    @property
 459    def is_alive(self) -> bool:
 460        return self._session is not None
 461
 462    @typing.final
 463    def _acquire(self) -> _Session:
 464        """Acquire a AIOHTTP Client session for this REST client.
 465
 466        This is means to used internally by the client.
 467        """
 468        asyncio.get_running_loop()
 469        if self._session is None:
 470            self._session = _Session.acquire_session(
 471                owner=False,
 472                raise_status=False,
 473                connect=None,
 474                socket_read=None,
 475                socket_connect=None,
 476            )
 477        return self._session
 478
 479    @typing.final
 480    async def close(self) -> None:
 481        if self._session is not None:
 482            await self._session.close()
 483            self._session = None
 484
 485    @staticmethod
 486    def _set_debug_level(
 487        level: typing.Union[typing.Literal["TRACE"], bool, int] = False,
 488        file: typing.Optional[typing.Union[pathlib.Path, str]] = None,
 489    ) -> None:
 490
 491        file_handler = logging.FileHandler(file, mode="w") if file else None
 492        if level == "TRACE" or level == TRACE:
 493            logging.basicConfig(
 494                level=TRACE, handlers=[file_handler] if file_handler else None
 495            )
 496
 497        elif level:
 498            logging.basicConfig(
 499                level=logging.DEBUG, handlers=[file_handler] if file_handler else None
 500            )
 501
 502    def enable_debugging(
 503        self,
 504        level: typing.Union[typing.Literal["TRACE"], bool, int] = False,
 505        file: typing.Optional[typing.Union[pathlib.Path, str]] = None,
 506        /,
 507    ) -> None:
 508        self._set_debug_level(level, file)
 509
 510    @typing.final
 511    async def _request(
 512        self,
 513        method: typing.Union[RequestMethod, str],
 514        route: str,
 515        *,
 516        base: bool = False,
 517        oauth2: bool = False,
 518        auth: typing.Optional[str] = None,
 519        unwrapping: typing.Literal["json", "read"] = "json",
 520        json: typing.Optional[dict[str, typing.Any]] = None,
 521        headers: typing.Optional[dict[str, typing.Any]] = None,
 522        data: typing.Optional[typing.Union[str, dict[str, typing.Any]]] = None,
 523    ) -> typing.Any:
 524
 525        retries: int = 0
 526        session = self._acquire()
 527        headers = headers or {}
 528
 529        headers.setdefault(_USER_AGENT_HEADERS, _USER_AGENT)
 530        headers["X-API-KEY"] = self._token
 531
 532        if auth is not None:
 533            headers[_AUTH_HEADER] = f"Bearer {auth}"
 534
 535        # Handling endpoints
 536        endpoint = url.BASE
 537
 538        if not base:
 539            endpoint = endpoint + url.REST_EP
 540
 541        if oauth2:
 542            headers["Content-Type"] = "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
 543            endpoint = endpoint + url.TOKEN_EP
 544
 545        if self._lock is None:
 546            self._lock = asyncio.Lock()
 547
 548        while True:
 549            try:
 550                async with (stack := contextlib.AsyncExitStack()):
 551                    await stack.enter_async_context(self._lock)
 552
 553                    # We make the request here.
 554                    taken_time = time.monotonic()
 555                    response = await stack.enter_async_context(
 556                        session.client_session.request(
 557                            method=method,
 558                            url=f"{endpoint}/{route}",
 559                            json=json,
 560                            headers=headers,
 561                            data=data,
 562                        )
 563                    )
 564                    response_time = (time.monotonic() - taken_time) * 1_000
 565
 566                    _LOG.debug(
 567                        "%s %s %s Time %.4fms",
 568                        method,
 569                        f"{endpoint}/{route}",
 570                        f"{response.status} {response.reason}",
 571                        response_time,
 572                    )
 573
 574                    await self._handle_ratelimit(
 575                        response, method, route, self._max_rate_limit_retries
 576                    )
 577
 578                    if response.status == http.HTTPStatus.NO_CONTENT:
 579                        return None
 580
 581                    if 300 > response.status >= 200:
 582                        if unwrapping == "read":
 583                            # We need to read the bytes for the manifest response.
 584                            return await response.read()
 585
 586                        if response.content_type == _APP_JSON:
 587                            json_data = await response.json()
 588
 589                            _LOG.debug(
 590                                "%s %s %s Time %.4fms",
 591                                method,
 592                                f"{endpoint}/{route}",
 593                                f"{response.status} {response.reason}",
 594                                response_time,
 595                            )
 596
 597                            if _LOG.isEnabledFor(TRACE):
 598                                headers.update(response.headers)
 599
 600                                _LOG.log(
 601                                    TRACE,
 602                                    "%s",
 603                                    error.stringify_http_message(headers),
 604                                )
 605
 606                            # Return the response.
 607                            # oauth2 responses are not packed inside a Response object.
 608                            if oauth2:
 609                                return json_data
 610
 611                            return json_data["Response"]
 612
 613                    if (
 614                        response.status in _RETRY_5XX
 615                        and retries < self._max_retries  # noqa: W503
 616                    ):
 617                        backoff_ = backoff.ExponentialBackOff(maximum=6)
 618                        sleep_time = next(backoff_)
 619                        _LOG.warning(
 620                            "Got %i - %s. Sleeping for %.2f seconds. Remaining retries: %i",
 621                            response.status,
 622                            response.reason,
 623                            sleep_time,
 624                            self._max_retries - retries,
 625                        )
 626
 627                        retries += 1
 628                        await asyncio.sleep(sleep_time)
 629                        continue
 630
 631                    raise await error.raise_error(response)
 632            # eol
 633            except _Dyn:
 634                continue
 635
 636    if not typing.TYPE_CHECKING:
 637
 638        def __enter__(self) -> typing.NoReturn:
 639            cls = type(self)
 640            raise TypeError(
 641                f"{cls.__qualname__} is async only, use 'async with' instead."
 642            )
 643
 644        def __exit__(
 645            self,
 646            exception_type: typing.Optional[type[BaseException]],
 647            exception: typing.Optional[BaseException],
 648            exception_traceback: typing.Optional[types.TracebackType],
 649        ) -> None:
 650            ...
 651
 652    async def __aenter__(self) -> RESTClient:
 653        self._acquire()
 654        return self
 655
 656    async def __aexit__(
 657        self,
 658        exception_type: typing.Optional[type[BaseException]],
 659        exception: typing.Optional[BaseException],
 660        exception_traceback: typing.Optional[types.TracebackType],
 661    ) -> None:
 662        await self.close()
 663
 664    # We don't want this to be super complicated.
 665    @staticmethod
 666    @typing.final
 667    async def _handle_ratelimit(
 668        response: aiohttp.ClientResponse,
 669        method: str,
 670        route: str,
 671        max_ratelimit_retries: int = 3,
 672    ) -> None:
 673
 674        if response.status != http.HTTPStatus.TOO_MANY_REQUESTS:
 675            return
 676
 677        if response.content_type != _APP_JSON:
 678            raise error.HTTPError(
 679                f"Being ratelimited on non JSON request, {response.content_type}.",
 680                http.HTTPStatus.TOO_MANY_REQUESTS,
 681            )
 682
 683        count: int = 0
 684        json: typedefs.JSONObject = await response.json()
 685        retry_after = float(json["ThrottleSeconds"])
 686
 687        while True:
 688            if count == max_ratelimit_retries:
 689                raise _Dyn
 690
 691            if retry_after <= 0:
 692                # We sleep for a little bit to avoid funky behavior.
 693                sleep_time = float(random.random() + 0.93) / 2
 694
 695                _LOG.warning(
 696                    "We're being ratelimited with method %s route %s. Sleeping for %.2fs.",
 697                    method,
 698                    route,
 699                    sleep_time,
 700                )
 701                count += 1
 702                await asyncio.sleep(sleep_time)
 703                continue
 704
 705            raise error.RateLimitedError(
 706                body=json,
 707                url=str(response.real_url),
 708                retry_after=retry_after,
 709            )
 710
 711    @typing.final
 712    def static_request(
 713        self,
 714        method: typing.Union[RequestMethod, str],
 715        path: str,
 716        *,
 717        auth: typing.Optional[str] = None,
 718        json: typing.Optional[dict[str, typing.Any]] = None,
 719    ) -> ResponseSig[typing.Any]:
 720        return self._request(method, path, auth=auth, json=json)
 721
 722    @typing.final
 723    def build_oauth2_url(
 724        self, client_id: typing.Optional[int] = None
 725    ) -> typing.Optional[str]:
 726        client_id = client_id or self._client_id
 727        if client_id is None:
 728            return None
 729
 730        return url.OAUTH2_EP_BUILDER.format(
 731            oauth_endpoint=url.OAUTH_EP,
 732            client_id=client_id,
 733            uuid=_uuid(),
 734        )
 735
 736    async def fetch_oauth2_tokens(self, code: str, /) -> builders.OAuth2Response:
 737
 738        if not isinstance(self._client_id, int):
 739            raise TypeError(
 740                f"Expected (int) for client id but got {type(self._client_id).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
 741            )
 742
 743        if not isinstance(self._client_secret, str):
 744            raise TypeError(
 745                f"Expected (str) for client secret but got {type(self._client_secret).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
 746            )
 747
 748        headers = {
 749            "client_secret": self._client_secret,
 750        }
 751
 752        data = (
 753            f"grant_type=authorization_code&code={code}"
 754            f"&client_id={self._client_id}&client_secret={self._client_secret}"
 755        )
 756
 757        response = await self._request(
 758            RequestMethod.POST, "", headers=headers, data=data, oauth2=True
 759        )
 760        return builders.OAuth2Response.build_response(response)
 761
 762    async def refresh_access_token(
 763        self, refresh_token: str, /
 764    ) -> builders.OAuth2Response:
 765        if not isinstance(self._client_id, int):
 766            raise TypeError(
 767                f"Expected (int) for client id but got {type(self._client_id).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
 768            )
 769
 770        if not isinstance(self._client_secret, str):
 771            raise TypeError(
 772                f"Expected (str) for client secret but got {type(self._client_secret).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
 773            )
 774
 775        data = {
 776            "grant_type": "refresh_token",
 777            "refresh_token": refresh_token,
 778            "client_id": self._client_id,
 779            "client_secret": self._client_secret,
 780            "Content-Type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded",
 781        }
 782
 783        response = await self._request(RequestMethod.POST, "", data=data, oauth2=True)
 784        return builders.OAuth2Response.build_response(response)

1097    async def read_manifest_bytes(self, language: str = "en", /) -> bytes:
1098        # <<inherited docstring from aiobungie.interfaces.rest.RESTInterface>>.
1099        _ensure_manifest_language(language)
1100
1101        content = await self.fetch_manifest_path()
1102        resp = await self._request(
1103            RequestMethod.GET,
1104            content["mobileWorldContentPaths"][language],
1105            unwrapping="read",
1106            base=True,
1107        )
1108        return typing.cast(bytes, resp)

1110    async def download_manifest(
1111        self,
1112        language: str = "en",
1113        name: str = "manifest.sqlite3",
1114        *,
1115        force: bool = False,
1116    ) -> None:
1117        # <<inherited docstring from aiobungie.interfaces.rest.RESTInterface>>.
1118        if os.path.exists(name):
1119
1120            if force:
1121                _LOG.debug("Forcing manifest download.")
1122                os.remove(name)
1123
1124                return await self.download_manifest(language, name, force=force)
1125
1126            else:
1127                raise FileExistsError(
1128                    "Manifest file already exists, "
1129                    "If you want to force download, set the `force` parameter to `True`."
1130                )
1131
1132        _LOG.debug("Downloading manifest...")
1133        data_bytes = await self.read_manifest_bytes(language)
1134        await asyncio.get_running_loop().run_in_executor(
1135            None, _write_sqlite_bytes, data_bytes, name
1136        )
1137
1138    async def download_json_manifest(self, language: str = "en") -> None:
1139        _ensure_manifest_language(language)
1140
1141        _LOG.debug("Downloading manifest JSON...")
1142
1143        content = await self.fetch_manifest_path()
1144        json_bytes = await self._request(
1145            RequestMethod.GET,
1146            content["jsonWorldContentPaths"][language],
1147            unwrapping="read",
1148            base=True,
1149        )
1150
1151        await asyncio.get_running_loop().run_in_executor(
1152            None, _write_json_bytes, json_bytes
1153        )
1154        _LOG.debug("Finished downloading manifest JSON.")

1159    @staticmethod

1793    def fetch_vendors(
1794        self,
1795        access_token: str,
1796        character_id: int,
1797        membership_id: int,
1798        membership_type: typedefs.IntAnd[enums.MembershipType],
1799        /,
1800        components: list[enums.ComponentType],
1801        filter: typing.Optional[int] = None,
1802    ) -> ResponseSig[typedefs.JSONObject]:

A RESTful client implementation for Bungie's API.

This client is designed to only make HTTP requests and return JSON objects to provide RESTful functionality.

This client is also used within aiobungie.Client which deserialize those returned JSON objects using the factory into Pythonic data classes objects which provide Python functionality.

Example
import aiobungie

async def main():
    async with aiobungie.RESTClient("TOKEN") as rest_client:
        req = await rest_client.fetch_clan_members(4389205)
        clan_members = req['results']
        for member in clan_members:
            for k, v in member['destinyUserInfo'].items():
                print(k, v)
Parameters
  • token (str): A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
Other Parameters
  • max_retries (int): The max retries number to retry if the request hit a 5xx status code.
  • max_ratelimit_retries (int): The max retries number to retry if the request hit a 429 status code. Defaults to 3.
  • client_secret (typing.Optional[str]): An optional application client secret, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • client_id (typing.Optional[int]): An optional application client id, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • enable_debugging (bool | str): Whether to enable logging responses or not.
Logging Levels
  • False: This will disable logging.
  • True: This will set the level to DEBUG and enable logging minimal information. Like the response status, route, taken time and so on.
  • "TRACE" | aiobungie.TRACE: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.

#   metadata: collections.abc.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any]

A mutable mapping storage for the user's needs.

This mapping is useful for storing any kind of data that the user may need.

Example
import aiobungie

client = aiobungie.RESTClient(…)

async with client:
    # Fetch auth tokens and store them
    client.metadata["tokens"] = await client.fetch_access_token("code")

# Some other time.
async with client:
    # Retrieve the tokens
    tokens: aiobungie.OAuth2Response = client.metadata["tokens"]

    # Use them to fetch your user.
    user = await client.fetch_current_user_memberships(tokens.access_token)

Returns True if the REST client is alive and False otherwise.

Enables debugging for the REST client.

Logging Levels
  • False: This will disable logging.
  • True: This will set the level to DEBUG and enable logging minimal information. Like the response status, route, taken time and so on.
  • "TRACE" | aiobungie.TRACE: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.
Parameters
  • level (str | bool | int): The level of debugging to enable.
  • file (pathlib.Path | str | None): The file path to write the debug logs to. If provided.

Parameters

723    def build_oauth2_url(
724        self, client_id: typing.Optional[int] = None
725    ) -> typing.Optional[str]:
726        client_id = client_id or self._client_id
727        if client_id is None:
728            return None
729
730        return url.OAUTH2_EP_BUILDER.format(

733            uuid=_uuid(),
734        )

Builds an OAuth2 URL using the provided user REST/Base client secret/id.

Parameters
  • client_id (int | None): An optional client id to provide, If left None it will roll back to the id passed to the RESTClient, If both is None this method will return None.
Returns
  • str | None: If the client id was provided as a parameter or provided in aiobungie.RESTClient, A complete URL will be returned. Otherwise None will be returned.

736    async def fetch_oauth2_tokens(self, code: str, /) -> builders.OAuth2Response:
737
738        if not isinstance(self._client_id, int):
739            raise TypeError(
740                f"Expected (int) for client id but got {type(self._client_id).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
741            )
742
743        if not isinstance(self._client_secret, str):
744            raise TypeError(
745                f"Expected (str) for client secret but got {type(self._client_secret).__qualname__}"  # type: ignore
746            )
747
748        headers = {
749            "client_secret": self._client_secret,
750        }
751
752        data = (
753            f"grant_type=authorization_code&code={code}"
754            f"&client_id={self._client_id}&client_secret={self._client_secret}"
755        )
756
757        response = await self._request(
758            RequestMethod.POST, "", headers=headers, data=data, oauth2=True
759        )
760        return builders.OAuth2Response.build_response(response)

Raises

762    async def refresh_access_token(
763        self, refresh_token: str, /
764    ) -> builders.OAuth2Response:
765        if not isinstance(self._client_id, int):
766            raise TypeError(

Insert a plug into a socketed item.

OAuth2: AdvancedWriteActions scope is required

Parameters
  • action_token (str): Action token provided by the AwaGetActionToken API call.
  • instance_id (int): The item instance id that's plug inserted.
  • plug (typing.Union[aiobungie.builders.PlugSocketBuilder, dict[str, int]]): Either a PlugSocketBuilder object or a raw dict contains key, value for the plug entries.
Example
plug = (
    aiobungie.PlugSocketBuilder()
    .set_socket_array(0)
    .set_socket_index(0)
    .set_plug_item(3023847)
    .collect()
)
await insert_socket_plug_free(..., plug=plug)

character_id : int The character's id. membership_type : aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.MembershipType] The membership type.

Returns
  • ResponseSig[aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject]: A JSON object contains the changed item details.
Raises
  • aiobungie.Unauthorized: The access token was wrong or no access token passed.

Edit a clan.

Notes
  • This request requires OAuth2: oauth2: AdminGroups scope.
  • All arguments will default to None if not provided. This does not include access_token and group_id
Parameters
  • access_token (str): The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
  • group_id (int): The group id to edit.
Other Parameters
  • name (aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]): The name to edit the clan with.
  • about (aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]): The about section to edit the clan with.
  • motto (aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]): The motto section to edit the clan with.
  • theme (aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]): The theme name to edit the clan with.
  • tags (aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[collections.Sequence[str]]): A sequence of strings to replace the clan tags with.
  • is_public (aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]): If provided and set to True, The clan will set to private. If provided and set to False, The clan will set to public whether it was or not.
  • locale (aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]): The locale section to edit the clan with.
  • avatar_image_index (aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[int]): The clan avatar image index to edit the clan with.
  • membership_option : aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.MembershipOption]] # noqa (E501 # Line too long): The clan membership option to edit it with.
  • allow_chat (aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[bool]): If provided and set to True, The clan members will be allowed to chat. If provided and set to False, The clan members will not be allowed to chat.
  • chat_security (aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[typing.Literal[0, 1]]): If provided and set to 0, The clan chat security will be edited to Group only. If provided and set to 1, The clan chat security will be edited to Admin only.
  • call_sign (aiobungie.typedefs.NoneOr[str]): The clan call sign to edit it with.

1652        return self._request(
1653            RequestMethod.GET,
1654            f"Fireteam/Clan/{group_id}/My/{int(platform)}/{include_closed}/{page}",
1655            json=payload,
1656            auth=access_token,
1657        )

Fetch a clan's fireteams with open slots.

This method requires OAuth2: ReadGroups scope.

Parameters
  • access_token (str): The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
  • group_id (int): The group/clan id to fetch.
Other Parameters
  • include_closed (bool): If provided and set to True, It will also return closed fireteams. If provided and set to False, It will only return public fireteams. Default is True.
  • platform (aiobungie.typedefs.IntAnd[aiobungie.FireteamPlatform]): If this is provided. Then the results will be filtered with the given platform. Defaults to aiobungie.crate.FireteamPlatform.ANY which returns all platforms.
  • language (typing.Union[aiobungie.FireteamLanguage, str]): A locale language to filter the used language in that fireteam. Defaults to aiobungie.crate.FireteamLanguage.ALL
  • filtered (bool): If set to True, it will filter by clan. Otherwise not. Default is True.
  • page (int): The page number. By default its 0 which returns all available activities.
Returns
  • ResponseSig[aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject]: A JSON object of the fireteams detail.

#   def fetch_application_api_usage( self, access_token: str, application_id: int, /, *, start: Optional[datetime.datetime] = None, end: Optional[datetime.datetime] = None ) -> collections.abc.Coroutine[None, None, dict[str, typing.Any]]:

1842        access_token: str,
1843        application_id: int,
1844        /,
1845        *,
1846        start: typing.Optional[datetime.datetime] = None,
1847        end: typing.Optional[datetime.datetime] = None,
1848    ) -> ResponseSig[typedefs.JSONObject]:
1849

1851        return self._request(
1852            RequestMethod.GET,
1853            f"App/ApiUsage/{application_id}/?end={end_date}&start={start_date}",
1854            auth=access_token,
1855        )

Fetch a Bungie application's API usage.

Parameters
  • access_token (str): The bearer access token associated with the bungie account.
  • application_id (int): The application id to get.
Other Parameters

  • start (typing.Optional[datetime.datetime]): A datetime object can be used to collect the start of the application usage. This is limited and can go back to 30 days maximum.

    If this is left to None. It will return the last 24 hours.

  • end (typing.Optional[datetime.datetime]): A datetime object can be used to collect the end of the application usage.

    If this is left to None. It will return now.

Example
import datetime

# Fetch data from 2021 Dec 10th to 2021 Dec 20th
await fetch_application_api_usage(
    start=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 10), end=datetime.datetime(2021, 12, 20)
)
Returns
  • ResponseSig[aiobungie.typedefs.JSONObject]: A JSON object of the application usage details.

#   class RESTPool:
View Source 
247class RESTPool:
248    """Pool of `RESTClient` instances.
249
250    This allows to create multiple instances of `RESTClient`s that can be acquired
251    which share the same connector and metadata.
252
253    Example
254    -------
255    ```py
256    import aiobungie
257
258    client_pool = aiobungie.RESTPool("token", client_id=1234, client_secret='secret')
259
260    # Using a context manager to acquire an instance
261    # of the pool and close the connection after finishing.
262
263    async with client_pool.acquire() as client:
264        await client.download_manifest()
265        return client.build_oauth2_url()
266
267    # Other people may acquire an instance from the pool.
268    async with client_pool.acquire() as client:
269        new_tokens = await client.refresh_access_token("token")
270
271        # Tokens now can be used from any pool.
272        client.metadata['tokens'] = new_tokens
273    ```
274
275    Parameters
276    ----------
277    token : `str`
278        A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
279
280    Other Parameters
281    ----------------
282    max_retries : `int`
283        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `5xx` status code.
284    max_ratelimit_retries : `int`
285        The max retries number to retry if the request hit a `429` status code. Defaults to `3`.
286    client_secret : `typing.Optional[str]`
287        An optional application client secret,
288        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
289    client_id : `typing.Optional[int]`
290        An optional application client id,
291        This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
292    enable_debugging : `bool | str`
293        Whether to enable logging responses or not.
294
295    Logging Levels
296    --------------
297    * `False`: This will disable logging.
298    * `True`: This will set the level to `DEBUG` and enable logging minimal information.
299    Like the response status, route, taken time and so on.
300    * `"TRACE" | aiobungie.TRACE`: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.
301    """
302
303    __slots__ = (
304        "_token",
305        "_max_retries",
306        "_client_secret",
307        "_client_id",
308        "_max_rate_limit_retries",
309        "_metadata",
310        "_enable_debug",
311    )
312
313    # Looks like mypy doesn't like this.
314    if typing.TYPE_CHECKING:
315        _enable_debug: typing.Union[typing.Literal["TRACE"], bool, int]
316
317    def __init__(
318        self,
319        token: str,
320        /,
321        client_secret: typing.Optional[str] = None,
322        client_id: typing.Optional[int] = None,
323        *,
324        max_retries: int = 4,
325        max_rate_limit_retries: int = 3,
326        enable_debugging: typing.Union[typing.Literal["TRACE"], bool, int] = False,
327    ) -> None:
328        self._client_secret = client_secret
329        self._client_id = client_id
330        self._token: str = token
331        self._max_retries = max_retries
332        self._max_rate_limit_retries = max_rate_limit_retries
333        self._metadata: collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any] = {}
334        self._enable_debug = enable_debugging
335
336    @property
337    def client_id(self) -> typing.Optional[int]:
338        return self._client_id
339
340    @property
341    def metadata(self) -> collections.MutableMapping[typing.Any, typing.Any]:
342        """Metadata dictionary."""
343        return self._metadata
344
345    @typing.final
346    def acquire(self) -> RESTClient:
347        """Acquires a new `RESTClient` instance from this REST pool.
348
349        Returns
350        -------
351        `RESTClient`
352            An instance of a REST client.
353        """
354        instance = RESTClient(
355            self._token,
356            client_secret=self._client_secret,
357            client_id=self._client_id,
358            max_retries=self._max_retries,
359            max_ratelimit_retries=self._max_rate_limit_retries,
360            enable_debugging=self._enable_debug,
361        )
362        instance._metadata = self._metadata  # type: ignore
363        return instance

Pool of RESTClient instances.

This allows to create multiple instances of RESTClients that can be acquired which share the same connector and metadata.

Example
import aiobungie

client_pool = aiobungie.RESTPool("token", client_id=1234, client_secret='secret')

# Using a context manager to acquire an instance
# of the pool and close the connection after finishing.

async with client_pool.acquire() as client:
    await client.download_manifest()
    return client.build_oauth2_url()

# Other people may acquire an instance from the pool.
async with client_pool.acquire() as client:
    new_tokens = await client.refresh_access_token("token")

    # Tokens now can be used from any pool.
    client.metadata['tokens'] = new_tokens
Parameters
  • token (str): A valid application token from Bungie's developer portal.
Other Parameters
  • max_retries (int): The max retries number to retry if the request hit a 5xx status code.
  • max_ratelimit_retries (int): The max retries number to retry if the request hit a 429 status code. Defaults to 3.
  • client_secret (typing.Optional[str]): An optional application client secret, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • client_id (typing.Optional[int]): An optional application client id, This is only needed if you're fetching OAuth2 tokens with this client.
  • enable_debugging (bool | str): Whether to enable logging responses or not.
Logging Levels
  • False: This will disable logging.
  • True: This will set the level to DEBUG and enable logging minimal information. Like the response status, route, taken time and so on.
  • "TRACE" | aiobungie.TRACE: This will log the response headers along with the minimal information.

212@attrs.define(auto_exc=True)
213class RateLimitedError(HTTPError):
214    """Raised when being hit with ratelimits."""
215
216    http_status: http.HTTPStatus = attrs.field(
217        default=http.HTTPStatus.TOO_MANY_REQUESTS, init=False
218    )
219    """The request response http status."""
220
221    url: typedefs.StrOrURL
222    """The URL/endpoint caused this error."""
223
224    body: typing.Any
225    """The response body."""
226
227    retry_after: float = attrs.field(default=0.0)
228    """The amount of seconds you need to wait before retrying to requests."""
229

32class UndefinedType:
33    """An `UNDEFINED` type."""

36
37    def __bool__(self) -> typing.Literal[False]:
38        return False

41        return 0

47        return "UNDEFINED"

49    def __new__(cls) -> UndefinedType:
50        if cls.__instance is None:
51            o = super().__new__(cls)

593def into_iter(
594    iterable: collections.Iterable[Item],
595) -> FlatIterator[Item]:
596    """Converts an iterable into an flat iterator.
597
598    Example
599    -------
600    >>> sequence = [1,2,3]

602            print(item)
603    # 3
