#   async def raise_error( response: aiohttp.client_reqrep.ClientResponse ) -> aiobungie.AiobungieError:
View Source 
241async def raise_error(response: aiohttp.ClientResponse) -> AiobungieError:
242    """Generates and raise exceptions on error responses."""
243
244    # Not a JSON response, raise immediately.
245
246    # Also Bungie sometimes get funky and return HTML instead of JSON when making an authorized
247    # request with a dummy access token. I can't really do anything about this..
248    if response.content_type != "application/json":
249        return HTTPError(
250            f"Expected JSON content but got {response.content_type!s}, {response.real_url!s}",
251            http.HTTPStatus.UNSUPPORTED_MEDIA_TYPE,
252        )
253
254    body = await response.json()
255    message: str = body.get("Message", "UNDEFINED_MESSAGE")
256    error_status: str = body.get("ErrorStatus", "UNDEFINED_ERROR_STATUS")
257    message_data: dict[str, str] = body.get("MessageData", {})
258    throttle_seconds: int = body.get("ThrottleSeconds", 0)
259    error_code: int = body.get("ErrorCode", 0)
260
261    # Standard HTTP status.
262    if response.status == http.HTTPStatus.NOT_FOUND:
263        return NotFound(
264            message=message,
265            error_code=error_code,
266            throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
267            url=str(response.real_url),
268            body=body,
269            headers=response.headers,
270            error_status=error_status,
271            message_data=message_data,
272        )
273
274    elif response.status == http.HTTPStatus.FORBIDDEN:
275        return Forbidden(
276            message=message,
277            error_code=error_code,
278            throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
279            url=str(response.real_url),
280            body=body,
281            headers=response.headers,
282            error_status=error_status,
283            message_data=message_data,
284        )
285
286    elif response.status == http.HTTPStatus.UNAUTHORIZED:
287        return Unauthorized(
288            message=message,
289            error_code=error_code,
290            throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
291            url=str(response.real_url),
292            body=body,
293            headers=response.headers,
294            error_status=error_status,
295            message_data=message_data,
296        )
297
298    elif response.status == http.HTTPStatus.BAD_REQUEST:
299        # Membership needs to be alone.
300        if error_status == "InvalidParameters":
301            return MembershipTypeError(
302                message=message,
303                body=body,
304                headers=response.headers,
305                url=str(response.url),
306                membership_type=message_data["membershipType"],
307                required_membership=message_data["membershipInfo.membershipType"],
308                membership_id=int(message_data["membershipId"]),
309            )
310        return BadRequest(
311            message=message,
312            body=body,
313            headers=response.headers,
314            url=str(response.url),
315        )
316
317    status = http.HTTPStatus(response.status)
318
319    if 400 <= status < 500:
320        return ResponseError(
321            message=message,
322            error_code=error_code,
323            throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
324            url=str(response.real_url),
325            body=body,
326            headers=response.headers,
327            error_status=error_status,
328            message_data=message_data,
329            http_status=status,
330        )
331
332    # Need to self handle ~5xx errors
333    elif 500 <= status < 600:
334        # No API key or method requires OAuth2 most likely.
335        if error_status in {
336            "ApiKeyMissingFromRequest",
337            "WebAuthRequired",
338            "ApiInvalidOrExpiredKey",
339            "AuthenticationInvalid",
340            "AuthorizationCodeInvalid",
341        }:
342            return Unauthorized(
343                message=message,
344                error_code=error_code,
345                throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
346                url=str(response.real_url),
347                body=body,
348                headers=response.headers,
349                error_status=error_status,
350                message_data=message_data,
351            )
352
353        # Anything contains not found.
354        elif (
355            "NotFound" in error_status or error_status == "UserCannotFindRequestedUser"
356        ):
357            return NotFound(
358                message=message,
359                error_code=error_code,
360                throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
361                url=str(response.real_url),
362                body=body,
363                headers=response.headers,
364                error_status=error_status,
365                message_data=message_data,
366            )
367
368        # Other 5xx errors.
369        else:
370            return InternalServerError(
371                message=message,
372                error_code=error_code,
373                throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
374                url=str(response.real_url),
375                body=body,
376                headers=response.headers,
377                error_status=error_status,
378                message_data=message_data,
379                http_status=status,
380            )
381    # Something else.
382    else:
383        return HTTPException(
384            message=message,
385            error_code=error_code,
386            throttle_seconds=throttle_seconds,
387            url=str(response.real_url),
388            body=body,
389            headers=response.headers,
390            error_status=error_status,
391            message_data=message_data,
392            http_status=status,
393        )

Generates and raise exceptions on error responses.

#   def stringify_http_message(headers: 'collections.Mapping[str, str]') -> str:
View Source 
396def stringify_http_message(headers: collections.Mapping[str, str]) -> str:
397    return (
398        "{ \n"
399        + "\n".join(  # noqa: W503
400            f"{f'   {key}'}: {value}"
401            if key not in ("Authorization", "X-API-KEY")
402            else f"   {key}: HIDDEN_TOKEN"
403            for key, value in headers.items()
404        )
405        + "\n}"  # noqa: W503
406    )
